<HEADLINE> Bangladeshi Opposition Begins Agitation Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The main opposition Bangladesh
Nationalist Party (BNP) today launched a month-long countrywide
agitation program against the eight-month-old government of Sheikh
Hasina.
</P>
<P>
BNP Chairperson Khaleda Zia, who was defeated in the
parliamentary elections last June, announced the program on
February 26.
</P>
<P>
It is reported that the BNP today launched protest meetings and
processions at district headquarters throughout the country.
</P>
<P>
In the capital city of Dhaka, the BNP held a meeting in front
of the National Press Club this afternoon, which was followed by a
procession. No severe violence was reported.
</P>
<P>
The opposition party pressed home some demands including the
release of detained partymen and withdrawal of the cases against
them, resignation of Chief Election Commissioner Abu Hena and
introduction of the voter identity card.
</P>
<P>
The BNP's month-long programs include countrywide mass contact
from today to March 29 and meetings and processions at county
headquarters on March 30.
</P>
<P>
The opposition also threatens to declare "tougher" programs if
the government fails to improve the present political and economic
situation and meet its demands by March 30.  
</P>
</TEXT>
