<HEADLINE> S.Korean President to Nominate New Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, March 3 (Xinhua) -- South Korean President Kim Young-sam
will nominate Myongji University President Koh Kun Tuesday morning
as the new prime minister to replace Lee Soo-sung, sources at the
presidential residence said today.
</P>
<P>
If the nomination is ratified by the parliament, Koh will be
the fifth prime minister in Kim's five-year term as the country's
head of state since February 1993.
</P>
<P>
The president and the new prime minister will then decide the
formation of the new cabinet, and a reshuffle of cabinet will be
made on Wednesday morning, according to the sources.
</P>
<P>
In the reshuffle, several cabinet members, including the deputy
prime minister in charge of economic affairs, and ministers of
justice, culture and sports, and construction and transportation,
are expected to be replaced, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
South Korea will hold presidential elections at the end of this
year, and Kim is not allowed to run for a second term under the
country's constitution. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
