<HEADLINE> McRae Wins Safari Auto Rally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Colin McRae of Scotland captured
his first victory of the season by taking the Safari Rally in a
spectacular showcase here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The former world champion set the fastest final stage to win by
seven minutes.
</P>
<P>
"I'm delighted and relieved," said McCrae who crashed his
Subaru through a wall on Sunday after avoiding rocks left on the
road by spectators.
</P>
<P>
Richard Burns, despite a puncture, drove his Mitsubishi into
the second place while Ian Ducan was in a Celica at third.
</P>
</TEXT>
