<HEADLINE> Asia Pacific Eye Care Meeting Opens in Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, March 3 (Xinhua) -- More than 500 doctors working in
the field of eye care from 34 countries are gathering in this
capital city of Nepal to discuss ways to improve and expand eye
care services in the Asia Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
The 16th congress of the Asia Pacific Academy of Ophthalmology
was inaugurated here today by King of Nepal Birendra at a function
in the International Convention Hall in Downtown Kathmandu.
</P>
<P>
According to organizers, the academy decided to hold its 16th
congress in Nepal two years ago to acknowledge Nepal's
achievements in eye care services in the last two decades.
</P>
<P>
The four-day event, with the theme "Reach the Unreached," will
be helpful in promoting direct interaction and exchange of
experiences between ophthalmologists especially those from the
Asia Pacific region, they said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a science exhibition was also inaugurated to display
tools, equipment and medicines concerning eye care and information
reflecting the progress in the field.  
</P>
</TEXT>
