<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Non-Communist Parties, Figures on CPC's Political Consultation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Non-Communist figures here
attending the Fifth Session of the National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), today
praised the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee with
Jiang Zemin at the core for its contributions to the building of
socialist democracy in China.
</P>
<P>
The CPC Central Committee had held a total of 100 consultative
meetings with non-communist figures over the past seven or more
years to the end of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Such consultations and close cooperations between the CPC and
other parties and organizations have contributed positively to
China's economic and social development.
</P>
<P>
The CPC conferred and consulted with other non-communist
parties and organizations before it made any major decision in
recent years.
</P>
<P>
As the party in power, the CPC often notify the non-communist
parties and organizations of major international and domestic
events, issues concerning national economic and social development
and the anti-corruption campaign, and the diplomatic work.
</P>
<P>
Every year, Jiang Zemin and other leaders of the CPC Central
Committee, would invite leaders of the non-communist parties and
organizations and figures without party affiliations to air their
views about united front, multi-party cooperation and major social
issues.
</P>
<P>
Cheng Siwei, new chairman of the Central Committee of the China
Democratic National Construction Association (CDNCA), said that
the third generation of the central collective leadership with
Jiang Zemin at the core are always ready to hear the opinions of
non-communists.
</P>
<P>
Sun Qimeng, a founder of CDNCA, said that the political system
of multi-party cooperation and political consultation led by the
CPC reflects China's characteristics.
</P>
<P>
Huang Qixing, vice-chairman of the Central Committee of the
Jiusan (September 3) Society, said: "Multi-party cooperation is
not empty talk but has profound and concrete contents."
</P>
<P>
Qiao Shi, member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the CPC Central Committee and Chairman of the Standing
Committee of the National People's Congress, earlier extended
invitations to the non-communist parties and organizations for
brotherly supervision over the CPC. 
</P>
</TEXT>
