<DOCNO> XIE19970304.0016 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EC Approves Acquisition of Air Liberte by British Airways </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission today
approved British Airways' (BA) 4.9 million U.S.-dollar bid for
French airline Air Liberte.
</P>
<P>
The EC said in a statement that it had examined the effects of
the transaction on concerned routes, in particular the
Paris-Toulouse route on which both BA and Air Liberte operate and
found no competition problems.
</P>
<P>
"The Commission has come to the conclusion that the
operation...does not create a dominant position on the common
market or substantial part of it," the EC said.
</P>
<P>
British Airways has promised to invest 440 million francs (86
million dollars) in Air Liberte on top of the purchasing cost.
</P>
<P>
Privately-owned Air Liberte, which operates mainly in the
French domestic market, has been under judicial receivership
since September 1996 after defaulting on debt payments.
</P>
<P>
British Airways made its bid last November in the hope of
increasing its share of the French domestic airline market. BA
operated in France mainly through its subsidiary TAT European
Airlines which it took over in 1996.
</P>
<P>
After the acquisition, BA will merge Air Liberte with TAT and
install TAT chairman Marc Rochet as chairman and managing director
of Air Liberte. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
