<DOCNO> XIE19970304.0018 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kongs's Economic Prosperity Guaranteed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Chinese government advisors from
Hong Kong said today that the Basic Law and the principle of "one
country, two systems" will provide a strong guarantee for Hong
Kong's prosperity and progress after its return to the motherland
in July.
</P>
<P>
"The economic prospect of Hong Kong will be very bright," said
Hu Fa-Kuang, a respected Hong Kong entrepreneur and a member of
the Eighth National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference, which is in session here.
</P>
<P>
Like Hu, many other CPPCC National Committee members from Hong
Kong said that they are very optimistic about the region's future.
</P>
<P>
The real estate and stock markets are bullish as economic
growth picks up speed, they said, adding that 45 percent of the
overseas companies in Hong Kong made their way into the region in
the last five years.
</P>
<P>
They quoted a survey as showing that the index tracking the
confidence of Hong Kong residents is rising steadily and more Hong
Kong people residing overseas have returned.
</P>
<P>
All these show that people are full of confidence in Hong Kong,
they said, explaining that such confidence is derived partly from
the fact that Hong Kong will enjoy independence in economic,
fiscal and financial affairs and with regard to tariff policies.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, experience in the past years has shown that Hong
Kong's economic development has been supported by the inland.
</P>
<P>
With Hong Kong's return to the embrace of the motherland, such
support will become more direct, they said.
</P>
<P>
The confidence of Hong Kong and international investors is not
based merely on Hong Kong's 1,000-odd sq km land, but mainly
because Hong Kong has backing from the motherland, they said.
</P>
<P>
Tsui Tsin-tong, a member of the Standing Committee of the CPPCC
National Committee, said that bright prospects of the motherland's
economy, which is expected to grow by an average eight percent a
year during the Ninth Five-Year Plan period (1996-2000), will be
the most powerful guarantee for Hong Kong's economic prosperity
and stability in the future.
</P>
<P>
The two economies of the inland and Hong Kong will get closer
after July 1 and the inland's Ninth Five-Year Plan, its Long-term
objectives for the year 2010 and its effort to accelerate economic
development in its central and western parts will offer broader
areas of cooperation between them, he said.
</P>
<P>
Safeguarding and promoting economic prosperity in Hong Kong is
in the interests of both Hong Kong and the motherland, he said.
</P>
<P>
Hu said that cooperation between the inland and Hong Kong under
the principle of "one country, two systems" will enable China to
score greater economic achievements in the next century.  
</P>
</TEXT>
