<HEADLINE> New Black Oil Company Formed in S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 3 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's black
business empowerment has gained a new momentum today with the
establishment of a new oil company, aimed at empowering a broad
spectrum of business interests of the country, said a source
today.
</P>
<P>
The new company, Naledi Petroleum, based in Johannesburg, will
be controlled and managed by black businessmen, said the source.
</P>
<P>
Naledi Petroleum is a wholly-owned subsidiary of Naledi
Investment Holdings, which is owned 77.5 percent by Naledi
Petroleum Industries and 22.5 percent by Sasol Oil, a leading oil
company of the country.
</P>
<P>
At its initial stage, the company will purchase 18 service
stations from Sasol and focus on marketing automotive fuels and
lubricants in Gauteng Province.
</P>
<P>
The company, planning to operate approximately 40 stations
within the next three years, will come into full operation by
mid-year. 
</P>
