<BODY>
<HEADLINE> OPEC Oil Price Falls Below 20 Dollars a Barrel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The average price of a basket of
OPEC crude oil fell below 20 U.S. dollars per barrel last week for
the first time since last September, the OPEC Secretariat said
today.
</P>
<P>
The average price for OPEC's basket of seven crudes dived 1.03
dollars last week to 19.19 U.S. dollars per barrel, below OPEC's
benchmark price of 21 dollars per barrel.
</P>
<P>
Analysts blamed the decline on the advent of warmer weather in
Europe and North America, as well as adequate supplies in the
market because both OPEC and non-OPEC oil-producing countries are
fully utilizing their capacity.
</P>
<P>
The temporary return of Iraq to the oil export market under the
United Nations oil-for-food deal has had little impact on the
overall market.
</P>
<P>
The oil price has fallen steadily from a monthly average
five-year high of 23.51 last December to 23.19 dollars a barrel in
January. The average price for February hasn't been announced yet
but is expected to be lower still. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
