<HEADLINE> Jiang Expresses Sympathy Over Iran's Quake </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
today expressed sympathy and solicitude over the losses suffered
by the Iranian people in a violent earthquake in northwest Iran.
</P>
<P>
In a message to his Iranian counterpart, Akbar Hashemi
Rafsanjani, Jiang said that on behalf of the Chinese government
and people, he extended deep sympathy and sincere solicitude to
the Iranian people in the quake-stricken area.
</P>
<P>
"I believe that the Iranian people, under the leadership of
their government, will surely be able to overcome the
difficulties and...rebuild their homeland," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Since an earthquake measuring six degrees on the Richter
scale rocked on Friday the Ardebil region, about 600 kilometers
northwest of the capital city Tehran, 965 people have been
confirmed dead, and more than 2,600 wounded, official reports said.
</P>
<P>
Some 36,000 people have suffered losses in 82 villages,
according to the Interior Ministry.
</P>
<P>
This was the second major earthquake shaking the country in a
month. On February 4, a quake of 6.1 degrees on the Richter scale
jolted northern Khorasan province, killing 86 people and injuring
hundreds of others. 
</P>
</TEXT>
