<HEADLINE> Li Ruihuan on Literary, Art Creation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Senior Party Official Li Ruihuan
said here today that literary and art workers should take Deng
Xiaoping's concepts on literary and art as guideline, and make
concerted efforts to promote the prosperity of arts and
literature.
</P>
<P>
Li, a member of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau
of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, and
chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), made the remark during
a meeting with members of the Eighth CPPCC National Committee,
which is currently in its fifth session here.
</P>
<P>
After listening to a dozen members's speeches covering a wide
range of topics, Li said it is key to the prosperity of arts and
literature that Deng Xiaoping's literary and art concepts be
closely studied, understood, and carried out in a down-to-earth
manner.
</P>
<P>
"Comrade Deng Xiaoping's series of expositions on art and
literature are an integral part of his theory of building
socialism with Chinese characteristics, and should become the
guideline for art and literary work," he noted.
</P>
<P>
He said special attention should be paid to Deng's speech at
the Fourth National Congress of Chinese literary and art workers,
which summarized historical lessons and experience, and defined
the direction for development of arts and literature in line with
the Party's general task and characteristics of art and literary
work in the new historical period.
</P>
<P>
"This speech led to the spring of arts and literature in the
new historical period, and put forth a series of important
concepts, which is still realistically significant today," he
said.
</P>
<P>
"So long as we keep on doing things according to Comrade Deng
Xiaoping's theories, arts and literature will become prosperous
and retain the spring forever," he said.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that literary and artistic creation now have
favorable conditions, as China's longstanding and brilliant
history, and the bustling life of reform, opening up and
modernization drive provide literary and performing artists with
ample, varied raw materials for creation.
</P>
<P>
He acknowledged that the people crave for a richer cultural
life and are thirsty for more entertainment, while modernization
of various media have facilitated spreading of artistic and
literary works.
</P>
<P>
"Having gone through vicissitudes and accumulated precious
experience, all people of the art and literary circle cherish the
current situation of hard-earned unity and stability. With joint
efforts, we will surely write more works to the welcome of general
public and to meet the people's growing ethical and cultural
needs," he said.
</P>
<P>
"Since the time for everyone is limited, and writers and
artists should produce more and better works that can withstand
criticism by the coming generations.
</P>
<P>
He finally expressed the hope that artistic and literary
workers will increase unity, pluck up their enthusiasm, go deep
amidst the life of the masses and dedicate themselves to artistic
creation and contribute still more in prospering the cultural
garden. 
</P>
</TEXT>
