<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Xinjiang Enjoys Ethnic Harmony: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- China's autonomy system for ethnic
regions has benefited residents of all ethnic groups in
northwestern China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, said the
region's top legislator.
</P>
<P>
Amudun Niyaz, chairman of the Standing Committee of the the
people's congress of the region, said local residents are
satisfied with the government's ethnic policies. Amudun is in
Beijing attending the current session of the National People's
Congress.
</P>
<P>
Since ethnic regional autonomy was established in Xinjiang 41
years ago, all the ethnic groups there enjoy harmonious relations,
said Amudun.
</P>
<P>
"Maintenance of stability and acceleration of economic growth
represent the common aspiration of people of all ethnic groups,
and are in their basic interests" he noted.
</P>
<P>
"Ethnic minority are never discriminated against in the region,
enjoying all the political rights granted by the Constitution," he
said.
</P>
<P>
All the main leading posts of governments and the people's
congresses at various levels in the region are taken by ethnic
minority people, he said, and all the ethnic groups have their own
representatives in government bodies.
</P>
<P>
He took the example of the Uygur people, the main ethnic group
in Xinjiang. Forty-two percent of the deputies to the region's
people's congress are Uygur people, who account for 41 percent of
the region's total population.
</P>
<P>
The autonomous region has paid much attention on developing
education, said Amudun. Apart from Chinese and Uygur languages,
which are in common use in the region, local ethnic languages are
used in different autonomous prefectures, counties and ethnic
townships.
</P>
<P>
He added all the ethnic groups enjoy freedom in religious
belief as granted by the Constitution, and normal religious
activities are protected.
</P>
<P>
Reform and opening-up have led people of all ethnic groups to
the path of common prosperity, said Amudun, and the vast majority
of the population have been lifted out of poverty.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that petroleum development in Xinjiang in recent
years have helped improve local people's living standards, and
some major projects under construction, including two railways and
a highway in the Takla Makan Desert, are to boost the living
standards of Xinjiang people upon completion in the future.
</P>
<P>
"Over the next few years, Xinjiang will contribute still more
in safeguarding social stability, ethnic unity, and promotion of
economic development and cultural and ethic progress," said the
chairman.  
</P>
</TEXT>
