<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Train Accident Kills 125 People in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 3 (Xinhua) -- A train derailed this morning in
central Pakistan, leaving as many as 125 people killed and about
450 others injured.
</P>
<P>
Five cars of the train, which was heading for the southern port
city of Karachi, skidded off the tracks early today outside the
rural station of Mirshah near Khanewal, northeast of Multan in
Punjab Province.
</P>
<P>
Doctors, paramedical staff, engineers and other specialized
personnel of the Army have been called out to provide relief to
the victims.
</P>
<P>
Helicopters of the Army were also rushed to the accident site
to evacuate the seriously injured persons.
</P>
<P>
Special information cells have been set up at several major
railway stations to provide first-hand information to relatives of
the passengers of the train.
</P>
<P>
Pakistani President Farooq Leghari expressed today his deep
grief and sorrow over the loss of lives in the accident.
</P>
<P>
In his message to the bereaved families, Leghari assured the
injured that the government would provide all possible help for
their recovery.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif earlier visited the site of the
accident and asked the local government to hold immediate inquiry
into the mishap.
</P>
<P>
He also ordered local hospital authorities and health
departments to ensure provision of the best possible medical
treatment to the injured.
</P>
<P>
Punjab Governor Tariq Rahim and Chief Minister Muhammad Shahbaz
Sharif expressed deep grief and sorrow over the accident.
</P>
<P>
Sharif directed the local health departments to provide best
possible treatment to the injured when he visited Khanewal today.
</P>
<P>
As the rescue operations are still going on, the death toll is
likely to further rise as some parts of the cars are still buried
in sand.
</P>
<P>
The cause of the tragedy has not been found so far, but some
reports suggested that some problem in the brake system of the
train may have directly led to the derailment.
</P>
<P>
The ill-fated train reportedly developed some problem in the
brake system just before approaching the Mirshah station, which
made the driver unable to stop the train, sources at the Khanewal
station were quoted as saying.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
