<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The capital of Pakistan's
Baluchistan Province, Quetta, was jolted by another tremor this
morning but there were no reports of damage to property or loss of
life.
</P>
<P>
The earthquake, which measured 4.5 on the open-ended Richter
scale, rocked the city at 7:25 a.m., the Associated Press of
Pakistan reported today.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the earthquake was located in the
Koh-e-Suleman about 140 kilometers northeast of Quetta.
</P>
<P>
It was the second earthquake after the Friday tremors which
killed about 60 persons in the province. Hernai Tehsil of Sibi
Division bore the brunt of the quake with 39 casualties.
</P>
