<BODY>
<HEADLINE> British Health Ministry Confirms 16 CJD Cases </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The British Health Ministry
announced here today that there are altogether 16 cases of
confirmed or suspected human version BSE or mad cow disease in
Britain.
</P>
<P>
In its regular briefing on cases of Creutzfeldt-Jakob Disease
(CJD), the Health Ministry said in a statement issued earlier
today that there were 13 confirmed cases of the new variant of CJD
and another three suspected cases.
</P>
<P>
"In definite cases the diagnosis will have been pathologically
confirmed, in most cases by postmortem examination of brain
tissue," the statement said.
</P>
<P>
The statement stressed that probable cases have not been
confirmed pathologically and some cases are never confirmed
pathologically because the relatives of patients usually refuse to
grant a postmortem examination.
</P>
<P>
British government scientists said that a likely source of the
new variant was eating beef products infected with mad cow
disease. 
</P>
</TEXT>
