<HEADLINE> Environmental Protection Law Urged in Addis Ababa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The Environmental Protection
Bureau of the Addis Ababa city today underlined the necessity for
an environmental protection law, saying that "the promulgation of
environmental protection law in the city is important to mitigate
pollution".
</P>
<P>
The bureau, since its establishment last year, has taken
measures to control land, soil, air and water pollutions in the
capital city.
</P>
<P>
According to a report here, Mezid Seid, head of the bureau
said his bureau has studied and submitted to the City Council the
framework of the law.
</P>
<P>
Mezid said the peaceful life of the society in the capital is
disturbed by the noises created by factories, airplanes, trains,
vehicles and music shops.
</P>
<P>
Air pollutions emanating from sewages and all sorts of waste
disposals, smoke from factories and residential quarters are all
threatening the well-being of people in the city, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
He added a gypsum factory which was reported to have emitted
pollutant was sealed off, and called on the public to join hands
in the efforts to avoid pollutions which affect everybody.
</P>
