<HEADLINE> S. Africa's Wholesale Trade Increased in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 3 (Xinhua) -- South Africa's wholesale
trade sales for 1996, excluding diamonds, amounted to 221.4
billion Rand (about 48 billion US Dollars), a 12.7 percent rise
compared to that in 1994.
</P>
<P>
According to figures released today by the Central Statistical
Services in Pretoria, the largest percentage in sales, in current
prices, for 1996 compared with 1995 was recorded by wholesalers
in livestock and farm produce, that is 25.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, sales of wholesalers in machinery and equipment
comprise 16.7 percent of the total wholesale trade sales#,
excluding diamonds, for 1996 showed an increase of 25.3 percent
over the same period.
</P>
<P>
Wholesales of miscellaneous goods, which have the largest
market share, recorded an increase of 14.5 percent in 1996.
However, this represented a decrease of 1.7 percent in real
terms.
</P>
<P>
The seasonally adjusted wholesale trade sales, excluding
diamonds, for December 1996 was also 1.8 percent higher than for
November 1996. 
</P>
</TEXT>
