<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanzania to Attend IORARC Meeting to be Held in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Minister of Foreign Affairs
Jakaya Kikwete will lead a Tanzanian delegation to attend the
first ministerial meeting of the Indian Ocean Rim Association for
Regional Co-operation (IORARC) to be held in Mauritius from
Wednesday to Friday.
</P>
<P>
A press release issued here today by the Ministry of Foreign
Affairs said that the ministerial conference will be preceded by
a meeting of senior officials.
</P>
<P>
The process towards the establishment of the Indian Ocean Rim
Initiative was mooted by Mauritius last year. Seven countries
later met to map strategies for economic co-operation including
the drawing up of the charter and work program for countries
boardering the Indian Ocean.
</P>
<P>
The seven countries include Australia, India, South Africa,
Kenya, Singapore, Mauritius and Oman.
</P>
<P>
According to the press release, the areas of co-operation
include trade, investment and economic co-operation and issues in
agriculture, tourism, science and technology.
</P>
<P>
Other areas of co-operation include communication and
telecommunication, air and marine transport.
</P>
<P>
"The case for an Indian Ocean Rim emanate from the fact that
all regions of the world have established one form of economic
co-operation or another," the press release said.
</P>
<P>
Tanzania along with other countries was invited to the second
inter-government meeting held in Mauritius last May. 
</P>
</TEXT>
