<HEADLINE> First Yemeni Women Congress Ends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANAA, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The first Yemeni national congress
of women, organized by the Yemeni national committee for women in
cooperation with the United Nations ended here today.
</P>
<P>
The congress opened Saturday under the theme of "toward
enabling women to engage in political affairs and development
plans."
</P>
<P>
The congress devoted its meetings to promoting several
targets, foremost among which is to create public consciousness
in the cause of women.
</P>
<P>
It also concentrated its works on ways and means to uplift the
status of women and play up the role of the national committee
for women.
</P>
<P>
In its final communique, the congress said it had dealt with a
number of vital issues related to women, including a review of
the national strategy for women prior to its ratification by the
government.
</P>
<P>
The congress also discussed government plans, public policies
and the executive program to make women an effective force at
family and society levels.
</P>
<P>
The final communique further underscored the importance of
tackling the phenomenon of poverty and its social, economic and
political repercussions, promoting government policies and
programs to overcome the problem of unemployment among women.
</P>
<P>
The communique stressed the importance of granting women the
right of employment in the various sectors, uplifting women's
political consciousness, guaranteeing their right to assume
leading posts in administrative, judicial and government
establishments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
