<HEADLINE> Thailand to Join World Employment Association </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Thailand today agreed to join the
World Association of Public Employment Services, which is under
the auspices of the International Labor Organization.
</P>
<P>
The Thai cabinet approved a proposal from the Thai Ministry of
Labor and Social Welfare to join the association at its weekly
meeting today, according to a press release from the Government
House.
</P>
<P>
"As a member, it will be beneficial to Thailand to get more
information and be capable to exchange information on labor market
with other countries," the report said.
</P>
<P>
Membership in the association, which was founded in 1989, will
enable Thailand to participate in related international meetings
and acquire more knowledge on market-force administration, labor
movement and employment opportunity, it said.  
