<HEADLINE> Thailand Sets Rules for Foreigners to See Officials </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Foreigners will be required in
principle to follow new procedures when they wish to meet
high-ranking Thai officials in Thailand, the Thai Government House
said today.
</P>
<P>
Under the principles approved by the Thai cabinet today at its
regular meeting this week, foreign ambassadors, consuls, envoys of
international organizations and other visitors to Thailand are
subject to the procedures, the Government House said in a press
release.
</P>
<P>
These people will proceed with their requests through the
channel of the Thai Ministry of Foreign Affairs if they want to
pay a courtesy call and have an official meeting with the prime
minister and deputy prime ministers.
</P>
<P>
However, foreign ambassadors may request an appointment with
ministers and deputy ministers by directly contacting the
ministries concerned.  
</P>
</TEXT>
