<HEADLINE> EC Approves Emergency Humanitarian Aid for Bulgaria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission (EC), the
executive body of the European Union (EU), said today it had
approved 1.1 million Ecus (about 1.27 million U.S. dollars) of
emergency medical and food aid for Bulgaria.
</P>
<P>
It said the medical aid, granted by ECHO (European Commission
Humanitarian Office), was aimed at helping fill the serious gaps
in basic medical supplies which exist in the hospital sector of
the country.
</P>
<P>
According to ECHO, medication and medical equipment will be
distributed by the non-governmental organization "Pharmaciens Sans
Frontieres France" in selected hospitals across the country.
</P>
<P>
Food aid, the distribution of which is assured by both the
Austrian and Bulgarian Red Cross, provides basic food stuffs such
as wheat, rice sugar and pasta. The main beneficiaries will be old
people living alone, the handicapped, children from the most needy
families and other vulnerable groups.
</P>
<P>
This EU assistance comes in addition to a recent 20 million
Ecus (23 million U.S. dollars) grant from the European Commission
aimed at relieving the neediest in Bulgaria, such as pensioners,
orphans and the handicapped. 
</P>
</TEXT>
