<HEADLINE> Chinese Press Urged to Safeguard Stability </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese press was urged today
to work for stability and promote economic growth.
</P>
<P>
In a panel discussion with members of the National Committee of
the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC)
today, Ding Guangen, a member of the Political Bureau of the
Chinese Communist Party (CPC) Central Committee, called on the
Chinese press to do a good job this year, focusing on two major
events -- Hong Kong's return to China and the convocation of the
Party's 15th national congress.
</P>
<P>
Ding also called on the country's press and publishing circles
to work hard to promote the country's modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
Ding, also head of the CPC Central Committee's Propaganda
Department, said the country's press and publishing circles should
adhere to the theory of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics put forward by Deng Xiaoping and the party's basic
line and work to provide an ideological guarantee for reform,
opening up and the modernization drive.
</P>
<P>
Ding said Deng Xiaoping, who passed away on 19th of last month,
paid great attention to reporting and publishing work and gave a
series of instructions in this regard.
</P>
<P>
"Comrade Deng Xiaoping emphasized that the press and the
publishing industry must serve reform, opening-up and the
modernization drive and that newspapers, radio stations and TV
stations should regard the promotion of social stability and
enhancing young people's socialist consciousness as their
regular, basic task," he said.
</P>
<P>
He urged people in the press and publishing circles to turn
grief into strength to make further progress under the leadership
of the Party Central Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core.
</P>
</TEXT>
