<DOCNO> XIE19970304.0099 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Egypt Issues New ID Cards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak
today gave the kickstart for emitting the new identity cards which
are issued according to the state-of-the-art techniques, carrying
the national serial numbers of all citizens.
</P>
<P>
During his inspection to the Civilian Affairs Department where
the new system is installed, Mubarak filled in the application
form and obtained his new ID, according to the Egyptian MENA news
agency.
</P>
<P>
In a few days, more Egyptians could get their ID cards, which
reportedly would be hard to forge but easy to distinguish the
namesakes.
</P>
<P>
Altogether 45 million Egyptians are expected to obtain their ID
cards from a number of mobile electronic registration offices
massed all over the country within three years.
</P>
<P>
The new national code system applys a unique number that the
person will have from his birth to his death.
</P>
<P>
It provides an easy approach to identify people with similar
names by including 14 figures for their birthdays, governorate
codes, insurance codes made by the computer.
</P>
<P>
The new ID machines can issue the code in less than one minute
according to the latest international specifications which
guarantee protection against forgery.
</P>
<P>
The pattern of the Egyptian ID, which employed the latest
German technology, is so very desirable that even the European
Union member states are eager to obtain for issuing similar ones
to the EU nations, according to local press.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Egypt has purchased about 75 electronically-equipped
vehicles which will tour various districts to collect IDs and
issue documents for citizens.
</P>
<P>
This project will enable Egypt for the first time to make an
accurate mapping of its demographic data and distribution and thus
to facilitate the government's decision-making process.
</P>
</TEXT>
