<HEADLINE> China's Project Hope Has Nearly A Billion Yuan in Funds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Project Hope, a national program
sponsored by the China Youth Development Foundation to help
students in poverty-stricken areas, has received 978 million yuan
in donations.
</P>
<P>
The program has helped 1,549,000 school-dropouts to return to
class and has established 3,634 primary schools, according to the
Fifth National Panel on Project Hope Supervision Day held in
Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
According to those present at the meeting, a national
supervisory committee was set up in 1994 and has sent supervisors
to nearly 100 cities and prefectures and more than 200 counties in
25 provinces and autonomous regions to cooperating with local
auditing departments, news media, and donors to ensure the
effective use of donations. 
</P>
