<HEADLINE> Qiao Shi on Education, Family Planning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Senior Party official Qiao Shi
said here today China will further strengthen education and deepen
educational reform in line with the education law and the strategy
of invigorating the country with science and education.
</P>
<P>
Qiao, a member of the Standing Committee of the Political
Bureau of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee,
and chairman of the Standing Committee of the Eighth National
People's Congress (NPC), made this remark during a panel with NPC
deputies from east China's Anhui Province.
</P>
<P>
After listening to speeches by a number of deputies, Qiao
affirmed the achievements Anhui had scored in recent years, and
stressed the importance of developing China's education.
</P>
<P>
"Comrade Deng Xiaoping placed much emphasis on education. As
early as two decades ago, he cited scientific and technological
progress as the key to modernization, which cannot be attained
without education," he recalled.
</P>
<P>
Since the reform and opening up started in the 1970s, he said,
China's education has scored marked achievements and made great
contributions to the country's development.
</P>
<P>
"Meanwhile, there are still many problems yet to be solved and
a lot of work to be done," he noted, adding that the new situation
has posed new challenges to education, and the further growth of
national economy and various social undertakings needs more
talents in modern science and technology.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, he added, education should be further strengthened
in line with the strategy of invigorating China with science and
education and the education law," he noted.
</P>
<P>
Concrete measures should be adopted to increase educational
input, and both working and living conditions for teachers
improved.
</P>
<P>
"If we keep on increasing the education budget a bit every
year, it is not beyond our ability to achieve the objective set by
the State Council for educational input at the end of the
century," he noted.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that various reforms of the educational
system should be deepened, saying that to meet the demand of the
market economic structure and the modernization drive, schools
should pay more attention to the improving the students' practical
capability and general standards.
</P>
<P>
Speaking of family planning, Qiao said it is the basic national
policy of China, which cannot be further developed without an
effective birth control.
</P>
<P>
"The past years witnessed a decline in population growth, but
the task of birth control remains arduous," he noted.
</P>
<P>
He said the government would make unremitting efforts to carry
out the policy of family planning, so as to control the size of
population and improve the quality of the people.
</P>
<P>
"This will greatly benefit our country and greatly contribute
to the future generations," Qiao said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
