and inaccuraies" about St.Petersburg in the report of the IOC
assessment commission on its inspection trips to all the 11
bidding cities.
</P>
<P>
The Russian Premier hoped the IOC president and also the
selection commission would attentively consider the Russian
comment on the report of the assessment commission.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin emphasized "Russia is firmly convinced that
St. Petersburg could and should be the capital of the Olympic
Games."  
