<HEADLINE> COMESA to Have Single Currency by 2020 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The Common Market for Eastern and
Southern Africa (COMESA) will have a unitary currency by the year
2020, according to a document of the regional organization.
</P>
<P>
It said that major progress has been made in the liberalization
of the exchange rates of the COMESA member states and it has
helped reduce the over-valuation of their currencies.
</P>
<P>
So far out of the 20 member states, 14 have market-determined
exchange rates while the others have managed floating exchange
rates or have single currency peg.
</P>
<P>
But only four member states have fully liberalized capital and
current accounts, 11 have liberalized current accounts and the
remaining countries still have restrictions.
</P>
<P>
Nine of the member states have market-determined interest rates,
two have a combination of market and fixed rates and some others have
their interest rates fixed by the their central banks, according to
the document. enditem

=03041423

