<HEADLINE> Ericsson Introduces World's Smallest PCS Phone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Swedish telecommunications giant
Ericsson today launched the world's lightest and smallest mobile
phone.
</P>
<P>
The new PCS (personal communications system) phone weighs just
135 grams and is 10 centimeters long and will be available in the
United States from June.
</P>
<P>
Known as the CF 788, it was built for the PCS 1900 system (GSM
North America) and offers users an array of new, customized
features.
</P>
<P>
Although the CF 788 is small enough to fit into the user's
pocket, it is big on power, with the batteries capable of
delivering three hours of talk time and 48 hours of standby
time. The CF 788 also has two vocoders (digital voice coders),
including an enhanced full-rate vocoder for superior voice quality.
</P>
<P>
The CF 788 has a flexible menu system that enables users to
create a totally personalized mobile communications
product. Consumers can choose between a simplified menu mode for
the functions they use most, or the fully extended 24 menu mode
for access to all available features. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
