<DOCNO> XIE19970304.0124 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shenzhen, Hong Kong To Have Closer Cooperation: City Party Head </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Cooperation between Shenzhen and
Hong Kong will be closer and the scope for their cooperation will
be broader after the latter's return to China, said the Party
chief of Shenzhen, the south China city adjacent to Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Li Youwei, secretary of the Shenzhen Municipal Party Committee,
said there exist four major differences between the two cities, in
social system, policies and operational mechanism, laws in force,
and the degree of market development.
</P>
<P>
He said, "Strict differentiation should be made of the
differences, and there must not be any ambiguity and confusion."
</P>
<P>
Li, who is here attending the ongoing session of the National
People's Congress, China's top legislature, pointed out, "The
first difference between Shenzhen and Hong Kong is one in social
and political systems. According to the principle of `one country,
two systems', Hong Kong will continue to practise capitalism while
socialism is practised in Shenzhen. This should by no means be
obscured."
</P>
<P>
Li added laws and regulations applying in Shenzhen comply with
the demands of the socialist system and a socialist market
economy, while Hong Kong's laws cater to the demands of capitalism
and a free port.
</P>
<P>
"However, we may use those in Hong Kong that are suitable for
SEZs as reference," said he.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong has a developed market economy, Li said, while
Shenzhen is still at an initial stage.
</P>
<P>
To help Shenzhen develop its market economy, he explained, more
cooperation and exchanges between Shenzhen and Hong Kong are
needed.
</P>
<P>
He cited four fields that have the greatest potential for
cooperation: city infrastructure such as water supply, land, air
and water transportation, the two ports of entry, and large
construction projects.
</P>
<P>
As the only inland city to border Hong Kong, Li pointed out,
Shenzhen is the hub and passage connecting the whole inland area
with Hong Kong, and successful cooperation between the two cities
will help promote that between Hong Kong and entire inland areas.
</P>
</TEXT>
