<HEADLINE> Drought Hits Suthwestern Somalia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Drought and famine have occured
in three areas of southwestern Somalia and hundred people have
reportedly died in the calamity, a report reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted the National Relief and Rehabilitation Committee
appointed by faction leader Hussien Mohamed Aideed as saying that
hundreds of people have died of hunger, thirst and diseases related to
malnutrition in Bay, Bakol and Gedo areas in the last two months.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, more than 80 percent of the victims were
children between 2 and 7 years old.
</P>
<P>
In the famine stricken areas, domestic animals particularly
cattle were dying in dozens due to lack of water and pasture.
