<HEADLINE> Northeast China Restructuring Industrial Product Mix </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, March 4 (Xinhua) -- A greater effort is being made in
developing new products and increasing production of popular items
in northeast China's Liaoning Province, to restructure the local
industrial product mix.
</P>
<P>
The traditional industrial base developed nearly 6,000 new
products in 1996, helping the province bring in nearly 18 billion
yuan in output value, an increase of nearly 16 percent over the
previous year.
</P>
<P>
Local authorities made preferential policies on funding,
energy, and transportation to give a boost to production of local
name-brand products, and Liaoning now has a total of 350 popular
products, which contribute more than 35 percent of the total sales
of the provincial state-owned industrial enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Of these, 50 popular industrial products are expected to
generate more than 100 million yuan in annual output value.
</P>
<P>
Local industrial enterprises at or above the county level
earned nearly 321 billion yuan in sales in 1996, up 10 percent
over 1995, selling more than 97.5 percent of their
products. enditem
