<HEADLINE> Southern Chinese Interested In Learning More About Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The people of south China's
Guangdong Province, which is next-door to Hong Kong, are showing
increasing interest in Hong Kong because of its return on July 1.
</P>
<P>
The people of the two places share the same dialect, customs,
and lifestyle, and have close economic ties, and as the date of
the return draws nearer everything related to Hong Kong interests
the residents of this province.
</P>
<P>
Local bookstores are profiting by the sales of all kinds of
books on Hong Kong, while local newspapers are competing with each
other to provide special columns or pages on political, economic,
and cultural issues in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, local governments and social organizations are
holding discussions on how to further bolster cooperation between
the two regions.
</P>
<P>
Sightseeing in Hong Kong has attracted many people in Guangdong
and offices of major travel agencies have been crowded with
applications for visits, and groups of local travelers can be seen
waiting at railway and bus stations, or ports, headed for Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
For local collectors, a vast array of bank-notes, coins,
stamps, and first-day covers issued by Hong Kong are considered
collectors' items. 
</P>
</TEXT>
