<HEADLINE> Philippines Launches Tourism Highway Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The Philippine government today
launched a tourism highway program in an effort to tap the
country's tourism potential, the Philippine News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The highway program will link the country's tourist areas
through a national highway system, from the northern city of
Laoag, via Manila, to Mindanao in the south.
</P>
<P>
The program will cover "scenic spot" portions of the tourism
highway to "showcase the splendor and beauty" of the local
landscape, as well as its tourist attractions, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine government also created a Presidential Task
Force led by the Department of Tourism to implement the highway
program.
</P>
<P>
A total of 950,000 US dollars will be allocated for the
operations of the task force in its first year.
</P>
<P>
The report said Philippine President Fidel Ramos has ordered
the completion of the project in time for the celebration of the
Philippine Centennial on June 12, 1998.  
</P>
</TEXT>
