<HEADLINE> Bangaldesh to Maintain Support for "One China" Policy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Bangaldeshi President Shahabuddin
Ahmed said here today that his country would continue to stand by
the Chinese government on the "one China" policy and human rights.
</P>
<P>
"The Bangladeshi government does believe that Taiwan as well as
Tibet is part of China's territory," the president told the
newly-appointed Chinese ambassador Wang Chungui, who presented his
credentials today.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the return of Hongkong to China on July 1 this
year, the president said, "It has set a good example for the
international community that historical problems can be
peacefully solved through negotiation."
</P>
<P>
Welcoming the Chinese ambassador, President Shahabuddin said
that Bangladesh values its relationship with China. "We are close
friends and neighbors," said the president.
</P>
<P>
The visit of Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina to China last
September was a milestone in the development of relations between
the two countries, he added.
</P>
<P>
The president also expressed his deep condolences over the
death of Deng Xiaoping, describing him as a great leader of the
Chinese people. 
