<HEADLINE> Sjoberg Pulls Out of Indoor Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Sweden's former world high jump
record holder Patrik Sjoberg has decided not to compete in the
world indoor championships in Paris this weekend, according to
local reports here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Sjoberg, 32, quited the Grand Prix gala in Birmingham, England,
last month after he was hit with a glass during a celebrities
party at a trendy Stockholm night club and needed nine stitches in
his face.
</P>
<P>
Sjoberg was now injury free but has had problems during the
winter with cramp in his calves and did not feel adequately
prepared to compete in Paris, the local papers said.
</P>
<P>
Sjoberg was planning to spend a few weeks in Marbella, Spain to
prepare himself for his opening appearance of the the outdoor
season in Hengelo in the Netherlands on May 31, the newspaper
said. 
</P>
