<HEADLINE> Largest Trade Surplus for Germany Over 6 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Germany last year registered its
largest trade surplus since 1990 reunification, which stood at
97.6 billion marks (57.75 billion U.S. dollars), compared with
85.3 billion marks in 1995, said official statistics released
today.
</P>
<P>
The exports rose 4.6 percent to 784.3 billion marks, while
imports increased by 3.4 percent to 686.7 billion, according to
the Federal Statistics Office in Wiesbaden. 
</P>
