<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Produces 780,000 Tons of Bread Wheat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia at present produces
780,000 tons of bread wheat a year.
</P>
<P>
According to a report from the Ethiopian News Agency, this was
disclosed here today by Getnet Gebeyehu, Deputy Manager of the
Institute of Agricultural Research.
</P>
<P>
Getnet said the production showed a five fold increase in
two decades.
</P>
<P>
With regard to maize, Getnet said, 60 percent of the maize area
in the country are now covered with improved varities.
</P>
<P>
He added that the development of three maize hybrids has saved
about 1.7 million dollars between 1986 and 1991 by replacing the
importation of the seeds.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia harvested 11.7 million tons of crops last year,
including maize, sorghum, barley and wheat. enditem

