<HEADLINE> Fortune Oil to Expand Investment in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Fortune Oil plc has decided to
pump in 51 million HK dollars (6.5 million U.S. dollars) to build
a new oil depot in southern China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
Barry Cheung, chief executive of the company, said the new
depot, with a storage capacity of 40,000 cubic meters, would help
Fortune Oil to become a direct supplier to industrial users in the
fast-growing province.
</P>
<P>
To be built in Jiangmen, Guangdong, the oil depot is expected
to become operational in May this year. With five tanks, it will
supply fuel oil to a local power plant.
</P>
<P>
It is the second investment by Fortune Oil in oil depot
facilities, following the first one in Shantou, Guangdong, which
will be completed by the end of 1997 at a cost of 34 million HK
dollars (4.4 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Headquartered in Hong Kong, Fortune Oil is a London-listed
company engaged in oil-related operations and investments. 
</P>
