<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Meet US Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) --An American delegation, led by
Barber Conable Jr., chairman of the National Committee on US-China
Relations, and Robert McNamara, former US secretary of defense,
who are visiting China, say there are broad prospects for US-China
relations, during talks with Premier Li Peng this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The delegation is here for activities commemorating the 25th
anniversary of the Sino-US Shanghai joint communique, as guests of
the Chinese People's Institute of Foreign Affairs.
</P>
<P>
Li said that the communique had great significance in Sino-US
relations and influenced the whole world, and that its provisions
still guide Sino-US relations.
</P>
<P>
"Comrade Deng Xiaoping made historic contributions to the
normalization of Sino-US relations, and his proposals on the
development of relations are still important principles in
handling Sino-US relations," he added.
</P>
<P>
China is pleased to see that there has been momentum in Sino-US
relations since the second half of last year, he said, and that
high-level exchanges of visits will help the development of
Sino-US relations, especially the state visit by President Jiang
Zemin to the US later this year and the state visit by President
Clinton to China next year.
</P>
<P>
Li expressed the hope that both sides will work together to
ensure smooth and successful exchanges of state visits of the top
leaders, and answered questions about the situation in China, its
entry into the World Trade Organization, and the Asia-Pacific
regional situation.
</P>
<P>
Conable said that the members of the delegation are dedicated
to developing US-Chinese relations. They came to China and worked
with Chinese friends to explore channels for further development
of the relations, he noted.
</P>
<P>
After extensive talks with Chinese officials and experts, all
of them said they saw broad prospects for US-Chinese relations,
Conable said.
</P>
<P>
He told li that they saw great changes take place in China and
deeply felt the great significance of Deng's policy of reform and
opening-up. China has remarkably raised the people's standard of
living in such a short time, he said, something that could not
occur in any other country.
</P>
<P>
He said that the National Committee on US-China Relations will
continue to contribute to improving the bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
