<HEADLINE> Another Bridge to Be Built Across China's Longest River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YICHANG, March 4 (Xinhua) -- A single-tower, cable-stay bridge
is scheduled to be built across the Yangtze River, China's
largest, in Yichang City, Hubei Province, where the giant Three
Gorges Hydro-electric Power Project is underway.
</P>
<P>
The State Planning Commission recently approved the six-lane
"Wulong" (Five-Dragon) bridge, which is designed at 2,460 m in
length, with an 840 m-long main span, at a cost of 880 million
yuan.
</P>
<P>
At present, the people of Yichang have to cross the river by
ferry, so the bridge is expected to help the expansion and
development of the urban area as well as the construction work on
the hydro-electric power project.  
</P>
