<HEADLINE> Philippines to Hold Asian Ladies Golf Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Eleven countries and regions, including Australia, China,
Thailand Japan and Hongkong, will each send a three-member team
for this annual tournament.
</P>
<P>
The format of the championship is a 54-hole stroke play over
three days with the best two gross scores to count each day for
each team.
</P>
<P>
There is also an individual event for the three-day combined
gross score and a daily prize for the lowest score.
</P>
<P>
Among the 11 participating countries, Australia and South Korea
are the power houses. Both countries won the Queen Sirikit Cup
separately for six times during the past 18 years.
</P>
<P>
The championship, which was inaugurated in Thailand in 1979,
was named after Thai Queen Sirikit who donated the cup. 
</P>
