<HEADLINE> Australian Casinos Nearly Double Profits in 1995-96 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Australia's 14 casinos generated
a gross income of 2.23 billion Australian dollars (1.74 billion
U.S. dollars) for 1995-96, with a pre-tax profit of 198 million
Australian dollars (155 million U.S. dollars) from 107.4 million
dollars (83 million U.S. dollars) a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
According to the Australian Bureau of Statistics today, the
gross income represented an increase of 36 percent over 1994-95
and the major source of income was from gambling of 1.88 billion
Australian dollars (1.46 billion U.S. dollars), which accounted
for 84 percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
At the end of June 1996, there were 18,490 people employed by
the casino industry, a rise of 17 percent since June 1995.
</P>
<P>
Yesterday, Sydney Harbor Casino, the biggest in the country,
reported a net profit of 48.9 million Australian dollars (38.1
million U.S. dollars) for the 12 months to December 31, 1996.
</P>
<P>
Average daily attendance during the December quarter was about
13,000 and it surged to an average of more than 15,000 a day
during the first two months of 1997.  
</P>
</TEXT>
