<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Stresses Adherence to Party's Basic Line (5) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jiang went on to say: "Over the past seven decades, our army
has marched from victory to victory, grown stronger and stronger
and withstood the test of complex environments and severe
struggles. The most fundamental reason for these has been the fact
that it has the powerful leadership of the Party."
</P>
<P>
"Our army has always followed what the Party says and is
utterly worthy of the trust of the Party and the people."
</P>
<P>
Given the important position of our army, the historical
mission it shoulders, and the nature and objectives of the
people's army, Jiang said, new circumstances require that we
enhance our understanding of the importance of Party leadership,
unswervingly persist in the absolute leadership of the Party and
follow the command of the CPC Central Committee and the Central
Military Commission.
</P>
<P>
Comrade Deng Xiaoping said that unity can only be realized
through having ideals and disciplines, Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
"Without disciplines as solid as iron, success cannot be
achieved either in revolution or in construction," he said.
</P>
<P>
With disciplines enhanced, revolution is ever victorious, and
this is true all the time, he said.
</P>
<P>
"In reform, opening-up and the modernization drive, we will
meet various complex situations and need to handle contradictions
and problems of one sort or another," Jiang said. "Therefore, it
is imperative to emphasize that the individual should submit to
the organization, the minority to the majority, subordinates to
their superiors, and the whole Party to its Central Committee, and
to further enhance the consciousness of observing disciplines. Our
army has always observed disciplines and regarded them as being as
important as life."
</P>
<P>
Observance to disciplines is a basic requirement of viewing
things from a political height and is an important guarantee for
keeping the army both centralized and united, he said.
</P>
<P>
Every comrade, all leading officials at various levels in
particular, should, under all circumstances, resolutely carry out
the decisions, directives, regulations and requirements of the CPC
Central Committee and the Central Military Commission, in order to
ensure a smooth implementation of political and military orders, and
no haggling is permitted, Jiang noted.
</P>
<P>
"We should do everything at all time in accordance with the
directives of the CPC Central Committee and the Central Military
Commission and in accordance with organizational principles," he
said.
</P>
</TEXT>
