democratic dictatorship in China, shoulders the important
responsibilities for safeguarding the state security and
maintaining social stability, he said.
</P>
<P>
Leading cadres at various levels, especially those high-ranking
officials, must be good at observing and analyzing problems from
political and overall angles and with the overall situation in
mind and do a still better job in maintaining stability, he said.
