<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Philippine Export Increases Slightly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Led by gains from electronics and
components, aggregate export earnings grew by 18.8 percent in
January to 1.69 billion U.S. dollars from 1.42 billion dollars
last year, the National Statistics Office said today.
</P>
<P>
But month-on-month, export receipts decreased by 10.4 percent
from the 1.88 billion dollars for December last year, according to
figures released by the office.
</P>
<P>
Representing 43.4 percent of the total earnings for the month,
receipts from electronics and components amounted to 732.9 million
dollars, up by 30.9 percent from 560 million dollars a year ago.
</P>
<P>
Articles of apparel and clothing accessories reported a total
income of 144.3 million dollars and was the second top earner
despite a 27 percent decline from 197.5 million dollars a year
earlier.
</P>
<P>
The United States was the biggest market for Philippine
products last month, with its imports from the country reaching a
total of 582 million dollars that month.
</P>
<P>
Other top destinations for Philippine products last month were
Japan, the Netherlands and Singapore.  
</P>
</TEXT>
