<HEADLINE> Fireworks Display to Mark HK New Airport Key Project Opening </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong is to stage a
spectacular fireworks display to celebrate the official opening of
the Lantau Link, a key project in the Airport Core Program, on
April 27.
</P>
<P>
Sponsored by Sun Hung Kai Properties Ltd., the fireworks
display costs some five million HK dollars (641,000 US dollars).
It will form part of the opening ceremony for the Lantau Link,
which was organized by the New Airport Projects Co-ordination
Office to mark the completion of the Airport Core Program
transport corridor.
</P>
<P>
Beginning at 8:00 p.m. and lasting for about 20 minutes, the
fireworks display will take two different forms. One form will be
as a fireworks waterfall flowing from the southern rim of the
Tsing Ma Bridge onto the see, while in the other form the
fireworks will be discharged from barges positioned to the north
of the bridge.  
</P>
