<HEADLINE> HK, Myanmar Sign Air Services Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The governments of Hong Kong and
the Union of Myanmar signed an air services agreement today, which
is the 17th air services agreement signed by Hong Kong so far.
</P>
<P>
Stephen Ip, secretary for economic services of Hong Kong, said
that there is great potential for the development of tourism,
trade and other economic links between Hong Kong and Myanmar.
</P>
<P>
"Direct air services between the two places play an important
role in enhancing our economic relations," he said.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out the importance of the air services agreement in
providing a firm and stable legal framework for the development of
air services between Myanmar and Hong Kong up to and beyond June
30, 1997. 
</P>
