<DOCNO> XIE19970304.0185 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ugandan Army Kill 791 Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The Ugandan government army has
killed 791 rebels of the Christian Lord's Resistance Army (LRA)
which aims to topple the government, since February 1996,
reported the local daily The Monitor today.
</P>
<P>
Defense Minister Amama Mbabazi was quoted as saying that the
remnants of LRA group led by Otti Lagony had to escape to Sudan
to avoid to the hot pursuit by the government army.
</P>
<P>
"We deployed around the border to prevent them from returning
to Sudan but they made it through before we finished the
deployment," he said.
</P>
<P>
Mbabazi charged that Sudan was likely to reorganize the LRA
rebels and unleash them on Uganda.
</P>
<P>
"We are also preparing for them," he said.
</P>
<P>
IRA was founded in April, 1987 by Joseph Kony, a 33-year-old
former Catechist in a Catholic parish.
</P>
<P>
The rebels fled northern Uganda in Sudan in October 1994 after
the government army intensified attacks on them.
</P>
<P>
In October 1995, LRA rebels fled deeper into Sudan because of
attacks from Sudanese People's Liberation Army (SPLA) led by John
Garang.
</P>
<P>
Between October 1995 and early February 1996, there were no
attacks taken by LRA rebels on northern Uganda.
</P>
<P>
However, on February 6, 1996, LRA rebels with weapons got from
the Sudan government entered northern Uganda again to start
activities aimed at destabilizing the region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
