<HEADLINE> Youngsters Building "Green Corridor" in Zhejiang Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, March 4 (Xinhua) -- A 250 kilometer "green corridor"
is being built along the Jinhua-Wenzhou Railway Line, which is
being seriously eroded by wind and rain.
</P>
<P>
One million young people, from factories, schools, army units
and villages, with various tools, have gathered on both sides of
the railway line to plant a million trees, reported officals in east
China's Zhejiang Province.
</P>
<P>
The project also marks a tribute to late Deng Xiaoping,
the chief architect of China's reforms and opening-up who advocated
tree planting movements in China 16 years ago.
</P>
<P>
The project has also enhanced the awareness of environmental
protection among the public, with local residents of all ages
voluntarily participating in the activity.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Provincial Governor Liu Xirong recently led a group of local
government official in planting trees with young people. Meanwhile, some
primary school students donated 8,000 yuan of their savings for
the greening project, according to provincial reports.
</P>
<P>
The Zhejiang Provincial Committee of the Communist Youth League
of China sponsored the three-year greening project, together with the
local railway companies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
