<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Stresses Adherence to Party's Basic Line (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"We should conscientiously safeguard the great unity of the
whole Party, the whole army and people of all ethnic groups and
push forward our cause with one heart and one mind," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Historical experience has proven that unity is of overriding
importance, unity is power and unity is victory, he said.
</P>
<P>
"So long as the whole Party and the whole army are strong and
united and people of all ethnic groups are strong and united, we
can stand up to the test of any storms and our cause will be
invincible," Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
Among unity of the whole Party, the whole army and people of
all ethnic groups, unity among leading officials of the Party, the
government and the army always plays a spurring and exemplary
role, he said.
</P>
<P>
Since the 14th Party Congress, the whole army has earnestly
followed Deng Xiaoping's directive about carrying forward the fine
traditions and maintaining the true qualities of the Red Army, and
unity in and outside the army has further consolidated, Jiang
said.
</P>
<P>
"We must cherish and safeguard, to the fullest extent, the
hard-won overall good situation and continue to do a good job of
enhancing unity," he urged.
</P>
<P>
The crux of strengthening unity lies in safeguarding the
authority of the CPC Central Committee and conscientiously keeping
in unison with the CPC Central Committee, ideologically,
politically and in action, he noted.
</P>
<P>
For a big party with more than 50 million members like ours and
a huge country with a vast territory, a population of 1.2 billion,
and 56 nationalities like China, which is undertaking the great
but arduous cause of reform, opening-up and modernization, if
there were not the united leadership of the CPC Central Committee,
there could not be a united will and united actions throughout the
country, China would become a pan of loose sand, and nothing would
be accomplished, he pointed out.
</P>
<P>
"To safeguard the authority of the CPC Central Committee is the
political behest of Comrade Deng Xiaoping and is where the
fundamental interests of the Party, the State and the nation lie,"
Jiang said.
</P>
<P>
"Persisting in the Party's absolute leadership over the army is
a fundamental political system of our army," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
