<HEADLINE> Australian Wool Production Expected to Fall Down </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Australian wool production was
expected to fall 2.4 percent this season and the estimated
production was 639 million kilograms, the Australian Wool
Production Forecasting Committee said today.
</P>
<P>
However, the committee said in a release that the production
would rebuild in 1997-98, reaching the target of 645 million
kilograms.
</P>
<P>
The committee said, "the 1997-98 forecast is based on average
seasonal conditions prevailing in most wool producing areas. If
the forecast is correct, it would reflect the first increase in
annual production since 1992-93."
</P>
<P>
Wool is one of the country's principal export products which
earned 1.85 billion Australian dollars (1.44 billion US dollars)
last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
