<HEADLINE> China, Philippines to Host ASEAN Group Meeting: Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Foreign affairs and defense
officials from 21 members of the ASEAN regional forum will gather
in Beijing early this month to discuss regional security matters,
Foreign Ministry spokesman Tang Guoqiang said here today.
</P>
<P>
Tang accounced at today's routine press conference that China
and the Philippines will jointly hold in Beijing from March 6-8 a
meeting of the Inter-sessional Support Group on
Confidence-Building Measures of the ASEAN Regional Forum, as
authorized by the forum's third Foreign Ministers' Meeting.
</P>
<P>
"The purpose of the meeting is to enhance the mutual
understanding and trust in an effort to promote dialogue and
cooperation on regional security matters," Tang noted.
</P>
<P>
He said the participants will discuss regional security
situations and confidence-building, and explore means of
cooperation in this regard.
</P>
<P>
Officials dealing with foreign affairs and defense issues from
21 members of the forum, namely China, the Philippines, Indonesia,
Malaysia, Thailand, Singapore, Brunei, Vietnam, Laos, Cambodia,
Myanma, Russia, the United States, Canada, Japan, the Republic of
Korea, Australia, New Zealand, Papua New Guinea, India, the
European Union, will attend the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The meeting will be co-chaired by Chen Jian, China's assistant
foreign minister, and Severino, deputy Philippine foreign
minister, according to Tang. 
</P>
