<DOCNO> XIE19970304.0195 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Nanning-Kunming Railway Nears Completion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Construction workers have been
working hard day and night on rail-laying and bridge erection for
the last 15 km of the Nanning-Kunming electrified railway project,
which is expected to be completed months ahead of schedule, say
officials in charge of construction.
</P>
<P>
The 898.7-km Nanning-Kunming Railway runs from Nanning in the
Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region in the east to Kunming in Yunnan
Province in the west. A section of the railway runs northward to
Hongguo in Guizhou Province. It is a transportation artery in
mountainous southwest China.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the project started in December 1990, and
completion is scheduled for 1997. The total investment of 6.5
billion yuan is shared by the central government and authorities
in Guangxi, Yunnan and Guizhou.
</P>
<P>
The electrified line has designed speeds of 80-120 km per hour,
a short-term carrying capacity of 10 million tons and a long-term
one of 30 million tons annually.
</P>
<P>
The Nanning-Kunming Railway is expected to help poverty
alleviation efforts in southwest China by turning the region into
an important base of power, coal, steel, gold and chemical
industries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970304.0196 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kenya's Counseling Program to Be Duplicated in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The International Labor
Organization (ILO) is to cooperate with Kenya to introduce the
Kenya Management Assistance Program (K-MAP) into other African
countries for promoting the small-sized business.
</P>
<P>
A draft proposal for an agreement between ILO and Kenya was
made to enable selected developing countries in Africa to
duplicate K-MAP model.
</P>
<P>
The countries which have been identified for duplication of
the K-MAP include Uganda, Eritrea, Namibia, South Africa,
Tanzania and Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
K-MAP which runs business counseling programs has succeeded
in solving problems hindering the growth of the small and medium
scale business sector.
</P>
<P>
Through the counseling programs, the private sector can aptly
meet such challenges as poor skills, concentration of the
businesses in the trading sector and poor marketing facilities.
</P>
<P>
The ILO/K-MAP cooperation will be focused on organization of
familiarization workshops for representatives of the selected
countries.
</P>
<P>
The two organizations will also arrange for joint regional and
country counselor training programs to facilitate networking
among management assistance programs.
</P>
<P>
The proposal noted that with many countries undergoing reforms
in the public sectors, the private sector would play a leading
role in economic development in these countries.
</P>
<P>
According to the proposal, duplication of this model should be
taken in countries where private sector development has been
identified as a priority and where governments have created
conducive environment for the private sector to take a leading
role in the economy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
