<HEADLINE> Nigeria Third Riskiest Place for Business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lagos, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria is the third riskiest place in
the world after North Korea and Iraq to do business, the "Nigerian
Tribune" reported today.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Godwin Omene, the Deputy Managing Director of
Shell Petroleum Development Company (SPDC), as saying this last
Thursday while speaking on Nigeria's oil and gas industry.
</P>
<P>
SPDC is a joint venture of the British Shell company and the
Nigerian National Petroleum Corporation. It is one of the major
foreign investors in Nigeria's oil and gas industry.
</P>
<P>
The deputy managing director called on the Nigerian government to
make conscious efforts to redeem the country's image so as to attract
more investment.
</P>
<P>
He listed several critical success factors that must be addressed
by Nigeria, which include observing international norms and standards,
stable governance with consistent and realistic policies, control of
corruption and improved education level, among many others. 
</P>
