<BODY>
<HEADLINE> McDonald's Company Expanding Business in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The McDonald's Company of the
United States is now operating 17 restaurants in Shanghai,
including one which opened just days ago in the city's downtown
area.
</P>
<P>
Local sources say that the U.S. company also plans to open 11
more fast food stores in this Oriental metropolis this year,
bringing the total number of the chain restaurants to 28 by the
end of the year.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the McDonald's Shanghai Center for Management
Training will also be established, designed to train qualified
workers for McDonald's restaurants in Shanghai and other cities in
east China.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. fast food company has been operating 128 restaurants
in 17 Chinese cities since it opened its first store in Shenzhen,
south China's Guangdong Province, including 30 in Beijing, 27 in
Shenzhen and 22 in Guangzhou, the capital of Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
McDonald's Company, which opened its first store in the state
of Illinois in 1955, has been expanding its business all over the
world, starting one new outlet every three hours.
</P>
<P>
The company has been operating 21,022 restaurants in 101
countries and regions, employing 500,000 people and receiving 32
million customers daily. The U.S.company did 31.8 billion
U.S. dollars-worth business last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
