<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Outstanding Women Tell Success Stories in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- A group of 11 outstanding women
from eight Chinese provinces told their tales of success in
Beijing today in their first of a series of public lectures.
</P>
<P>
The women's stories represent the fine qualities of
self-respect, self-confidence, self-support and self-improvement
that have contributed to their achievements, said Huang Qizao,
vice-chairman of the All-China Women's Federation, which
co-sponsored the series with central government organizations.
</P>
<P>
Xu Guangping, a street sweeper in Xuzhou City, east China's
Jiangsu Province, heads a team of nine female colleagues who work
in the city.
</P>
<P>
Although her work is strenuous, she said: "I would sacrifice
my own hope of the chance for clean work, so that others will have
a clean environment."
</P>
<P>
Pei Lijing, 22, opened a modern pig farm with 4,000 pigs in her
native village in east China's Shandong Province, after her
graduation from the Shandong University of Agriculture.
</P>
<P>
"I don't think the country gave me my college education just to
enable me to find a comfortable job in the city," she said. "What
I want to do is to contribute more to my village."
</P>
<P>
Last year, her farm turned over more than 400,000 yuan (48,000
US dollars) in profit and she has invested 20,000 yuan to support
200 pig-raising farmers in neighboring areas.
</P>
<P>
Chen Saijuan, deputy director of the Shanghai Hematology
Institute, was formerly a textile worker in Shanghai. Her research
in the treatment of leukemia has made some major breakthroughs in
the field which have been recognized both at home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
"I will devote my life to the study of leukemia," Chen said,
"and I will try to achieve this goal in my homeland."
</P>
<P>
As a student in France, Chen turned down the invitation from
the French science community for various high-salary positions,
and returned to China as soon as her studies were complete.
</P>
<P>
Huang Qizao called on the women all over the country to follow
the examples of the speakers, who have improved themselves and
made great accomplishments as a result of hard work.
</P>
<P>
About 1,000 people attended today's lecture.
</P>
<P>
The group will spend the next several days speaking in Beijing,
Tianjin and Shanghai. The tour will end four days after the
International Women's Day, which is on March 8. 
</P>
</TEXT>
