<HEADLINE> Palestinian Security Agent Killed In Gaza </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, March 4 (Xinhua) -- A Palestinian Preventive
Security agent was killed and another one wounded this morning,
according to a report of JMCC, a Palestinian press service
based in East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The incident took place in Deir Al Balah Refugee Camp in
the Gaza Strip when three unknown gunmen opened fire against
the two Palestinian security men. The two were identified as
Lieutenent Ismail Hasune and Paarat Abu Samak.
</P>
<P>
Hasune was a member of Fatah Hawks during the intifada (uprising)
period in the late 1980s.
</P>
<P>
The incident came at a time when tensions are running
high between the Israelis and the Palestinians as a result of
the Israeli government decision to establish a new Jewish
settlement at Har Homa in the Arab East Jerusalem. 
</P>
</TEXT>
