<HEADLINE> Expo'99 Kunming Solicits Emblem, Mascot, Song </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The Organizing Committee of the
1999 World Expo' of Horticulture, to be held in southwest China's
Kunming, has issued a nationwide call for suggestions for an
emblem, mascot and song to represent the event's theme of "Mankind
and Nature."
</P>
<P>
Kunming, the capital of Yunnan Province, is known for its
spring-like weather the year round.
</P>
<P>
The first such exposition was held in London in 1851. The 1999
expo will be held with approval from the International Bureau of
Expositions and the World Association of Producers of Horticulture.
</P>
<P>
The deadline for entries for the emblem and mascot is April 30,
and June 20 for the song. 
</P>
</TEXT>
