<HEADLINE> Share Prices Fall Lower on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Share prices declined on the
Singapore market in dull trading today as the benchmark Straits
Times Industrials Index fell by 6.9 points to close at 2,189.44
points.
</P>
<P>
Total market volume was thin at 284.38 million units, worth
498.45 million Singapore dollars (about 351.02 million US
dollars). Declines overwhelmed advances by 301 to 57, while 246
other counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Local fruit and food producer FHTK continued to be the most
actively traded stock as it registered a turnover of 20.92 million
units. It was followed by MBF Holdings which had 14.84 million
shares traded. MBF Land was next with 7.37 million of its shares
changed hands.
</P>
<P>
The Singapore Press Holdings (SPH) Foreign led the gainers of
the day as it rose by 60 cents to finish at 28.4 Singapore
dollars. The United Overseas Bank (UOB) Foreign increased by 40
cents to 15.9 Singapore dollars, while GE Life and the Overseas
Union Bank (OUB) Foreign ended 30 cents higher at 25.3 US dollars
and 10.7 Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Creative 50 and UMW warrant shared the top
spot on the losers' list as each of them declined by 40 cents to
close at 17.3 and four Singapore dollars respectively. Boustead
fell by 28 cents to 3.5 dollars, while Westmont Land was 26 cents
lower at 3.7 dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
