<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Sends Letter of Consolation to Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng today sent
a message of consolation to Pakistan Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif
over the recent earthquakes in the country's northern Baluchistan
province.
</P>
<P>
Li said in the message that he was shocked to heard that the
earthquakes in Baluchistan province and its capital Quetta have
caused heavy casualties and serious property damage.
</P>
<P>
On his own behalf and on behalf of the Chinese government and
the Chinese people, Li extended profound sympathy and sincere
solicitude to the Pakistan people living in the disaster area.
</P>
<P>
The earthquakes, which measured 6.3 and 7.3 on the Richter
scale, hit Quetta valley and other parts of Baluchistan province
on February 28, killing at least 49 people and injured about 125.
</P>
<P>
Premier Li said he believed that under the leadership of Prime
Minister Sharif and the Pakistan government, people in the
quake-afflicted province will conquer the disasters and rebuild
their homes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
