<HEADLINE> International Auto Show Kicks off in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- "Automechanika China", also known
as the China International Trade Fair for Car Workshop and Service
Station Equipment, Auto Spare Parts and Accessories, was opened
here today.
</P>
<P>
Sponsored by Messe Frankfurt, the CIEC Exhibition Company
(H.K.) Ltd. and the China Automobile Maintenance and Repair
Equipment Professional Association, the trade fair aims to provide
a venue for Chinese and foreign exhibitors to promote their
corporate image, swap experiences and jointly develop the Chinese
automotive market.
</P>
<P>
At Automechanika China, exhibitors offer a wide range of
products and services including automotive parts and accessories,
original equipment parts for garage, workshop and service station
equipment, vehicle service and care, services for the automotive
trade and environmental protection, recycling and disposal systems.
</P>
<P>
Quoting the British Department of Trade and Industry, Udo
Traege, a manager with Messe Frankfurt, said that "China's
automotive components market will be the world's biggest by 2005,
worth 45 billion US dollars."
</P>
<P>
In face of the enormous potential, international auto makers
are displaying a strong interest in the Chinese market with its
1.2 billion people.  
</P>
</TEXT>
