<HEADLINE> Official on Popular Feelings in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Describing popular feelings on the
future of Hong Kong, a Chinese official in charge of Hong Kong
affairs said, "When one is tired of Hong Kong, one is tired of
prosperity."
</P>
<P>
Chen Ziying, deputy director of the Hong Kong and Macao Affairs
Office of the State Council and a member of the National Committee
of the Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC),
improvised the dictum, imitating Charles Dickens' famous comment
about London that if one was tired of the city, one was tired of
life, at a group discussion attended by CPPCC members from Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
His remark was greeted by enthusiastic applause.
</P>
<P>
"Under the guidance of the great principle of `one country, two
systems' initiated by Deng Xiaoping, under the leadership of the
central authorities with Party General Secretary Jiang Zemin at
the core, with the backing of inland areas, and under the
direction of the chief executive elected by the Hong Kong people,
a smooth transfer of Hong Kong's political power and its
successful return to the motherland are assured," Chen said.
</P>
<P>
At the Global Panel held last November in the Netherlands and
the World Economic Forum held last January in Switzerland, Chen
said, international political figures, scholars and entrepreneurs
all expressed their confidence in the future of Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The chief executives of many international financial houses and
multinational corporations expressed their intention to increase
their investment and establish new representative offices in Hong
Kong at the forums, he said.
</P>
<P>
Chen pointed out, "The international community in the main
expects Hong Kong to fair even better in the future."  
</P>
</TEXT>
