<HEADLINE> Members of Advisory Body Submit Proposals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Members of China's top advisory
body attending an annual meeting here are active and enthusiastic
about submitting proposals for the government.
</P>
<P>
The members attending the fifth session of the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC), which opened on February 27, had offered 813
proposals by 5:00 PM Monday. Estimates put total proposals at
around 2,000 when the deadline for submission arrives on 5:00 PM
of March 7.
</P>
<P>
An official in charge of proposal submission said that the
proposals so far received cover a wide range of topics, with most
of them involving a sustained, rapid and healthy development of
the national economy and on promoting industrial restructuring and
state-owned enterprise upgrading.
</P>
<P>
The proposals are also related to promotion of socialist
ethical and cultural progress and the advancement of science,
technology, education, public health and sports.
</P>
<P>
The CPPCC National Committee members also aired their views and
raised suggestions on the advisory body's work last year and on
political consultations, democratic supervision and participation
in state and government affairs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
