<BODY>
<HEADLINE> C'Wealth Learning President To Visit Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The president of the
Commonwealth of Learning based in Vancouver, Canada, Professor
Gajaraj Dhanarajan, will visit Tanzania as a guest of the Open
University of Tanzania (OUT) from March 8 to 12.
</P>
<P>
According to a statement by a senior official of Tanzania Open
University today, Professor Dhanarajan would hold discussions
with Tanzanian Ministers for Education and Culture, and Science,
Technology and Higher Education in the country.
</P>
<P>
He will also meet representatives of the United Nations
Development Program (UNDP) and United Nations Chilldren's Fund
(UNICEF).
</P>
<P>
The statement said that Professor Dhanarajan is also scheduled
to inaugurate the Dar es Salaam Regional Center of the OUT on the
outskirts of Dar es Salaam and conduct a seminar for staff of the
OUT and other interested parties on March 12.
</P>
<P>
Professor Dhanarajan was a member of the executive committee
of the international Council for Distance Education from 1987 to
1992 before becoming Secretary General of the Asian Association
of Open Universities. He was appointed President of the
Commonwealth of Learning in 1995.
</P>
<P>
The Commonwealth of Learning is an international organization
whose aim is to create a widen access to opportunities for
learning by promotion of cooperation between universities,
colleges and other education institutions throughout the
Commonwealth, the statement noted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
