<HEADLINE> Dalai's Visit to Taiwan To Harm Ties Across the Straits: Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Foreign Ministry spokesman Tang
Guoqiang today warned that the Dalai Lama's upcoming visit to
Taiwan will undermine China's reunification and the relations
across the straits.
</P>
<P>
The Dalai Lama is not an ordinary religious figure, but a
political exile who has long been engaged in activities abroad
aimed at splitting the motherland, Tang said at a press conference
in response to a question on the issue.
</P>
<P>
The political motive for the Dalai's visit to Taiwan is
obvious, and the Taiwan authorities are also clear about it, the
spokesman added.
</P>
<P>
"No matter in whatever name the Taiwan authorities invite the
Dalai Lama," Tang said, "his visit will be harmful to the nation's
reunification and the healthy development of relation across the
Taiwan straits."  
</P>
</TEXT>
