<HEADLINE> Sydney to Set up Olympic 2000 Transport Body </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Sydney 2000 Olympics organisers
announced on Tuesday that a central body would co-ordinate
transport needs to avoid the problems that troubled the Atlanta
Games.
</P>
<P>
According to Reuter, Olympics Minister Michael Knight said the
newly-created Olympics Roads and Transport Authority would manage
road, rail and ferry services during the Games.
</P>
<P>
The Transport Authority would ensure the athletes, officials
taking part in the Olympics reached the venues on time and at the
same time the transport system operated smoothly for other users.
</P>
<P>
In 1996 the IOC listed transport as a major challenge for
Sydney. The city plans to use rail and buses to take most
spectators to the venues located in the city's west. 
</P>
