<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Huge Fire Guts Pretoria City Council Building </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 4 (Xinhua) -- More than half of the
Pretoria City Council's administration complex, the Munitoria
Building, was destroyed by a huge fire on Monday night, said a
source here today.
</P>
<P>
The fire, first detected at about 6.15 p.m. on Monday, was
finally brought under control this morning, nearly 12 hours after
it broke out in the building.
</P>
<P>
About 250 fire-fighters, with the help of troops from an air
force base near Pretoria, struggled into the early hours today to
contain the fire.
</P>
<P>
Five firemen were injured and admitted to hospital, where
their condition was described as being stable.
</P>
<P>
According to Pretoria fire brigade spokesman Johan Pieterse,
the fire broke out in the four-storey west wing of the building
and rapidly spread to the adjacent eight-storey north wing.
</P>
<P>
The fire completely destroyed the entire west wing, which is
housing the tax, licensing, and water and electricity
departments, most of the northern block and left the southern
block with severe smoke and water damage.
</P>
<P>
Pieterse said this was the worst fire in Pretoria since the
top 10 floors of the South African Agricultural Union building
were gutted in 1994.
</P>
<P>
Pretoria town clerk Henry Enslin said earlier that the
Council's 5,000 office workers would have to stay at home today,
but he called on residents to pay their municipal accounts at
other pay stations.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, City Council spokesman Tommy Thomson said although
most council administration records were stored elsewhere, data
captured since August last year, including vehicle registrations
and electricity payments, might have been lost.
</P>
<P>
A police spokesman said the cause of the fire was under
investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
