<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-04 09:21 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Turkey Plans to Buy Ships From Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Turkish Navy is preparing to
purchase four tug boats, three fire-fighting boats and four
high-speed landing craft from Russia worth about 50 million
U.S. dollars, local newspaper Daily News reported today.
</P>
<P>
"The need for such vessels has emerged as a matter of urgency
for the Turkish Navy because of its lack of adequate vessels in
Turkey," the paper quoted Turkish military sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
The recent oil tanker disaster in the Tuzla district of
Istanbul where two fire-fighters died has forced the Turkish Navy
to take serious measures to prepare for a fire on board a ship in
the future.
</P>
<P>
The sources added that the Turkish Navy also needs to renew
its fleet of vessels with landing ability, stressing that they
must catch up with new technology to "meet the demands of the
21st century."
</P>
<P>
A Turkish delegation will go to Russia to inspect vessels in
a bid to prepare a report for Turkey's plan.
</P>
<P>
Turkey and Russia are expected to reach an agreement on the
purchase of the Russian vessels soon, said the sources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
