<HEADLINE> Book on Zhou Enlai's Chronicles to Be Published </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- "The Chronicle of Zhou Enlai's
Life," covering the years of the late Chinese Premier's life
from 1949 to 1976, will be published soon by the Central
Literature Publishing House.
</P>
<P>
The three-volume book, which contains 1.56 million Chinese
characters, was compiled by the Party Literature Research Center
of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Based on the plentiful supply of archives and other materials,
the book will give a detailed account of Zhou's major accomplishments,
contributions and ideas when he served as a vice-chairman of the
CPC Central Committee and the premier of the State Council after
the founding of the People Republic of China in 1949.
</P>
<P>
As a key member of the first-generation leadership of the CPC,
he undertook the complicated search for a socialist path that
would be best suited to specific conditions in China, while
exerting his wholehearted devotion to the interests of the Party,
the state and the people, according to the book.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the book will recall Zhou's diligence and competence
in dealing with a myriad of state affairs in order to revitalize
the Chinese nation.
</P>
<P>
Reviewing the achievements and setbacks that occurred in the
course of socialist construction, carried out by the Chinese
people under the CPC leadership, readers will be able to
understand Zhou's significant work in making and implementing some
policy decisions in such areas as politics, military affairs,
economic construction, foreign affairs, science and technology,
the united work front and culture.
</P>
<P>
Most of the materials used in the book came from the Central
Archives, documents collected by Party and state departments, and
Zhou's diary, most of which will be published for the first time in
this collection.
</P>
<P>
Also included in the book will be articles, diary entries and
interviews with people who had worked with Zhou or had contacts
with him.
</P>
<P>
Compilers said the book provides abundant, detailed and
accurate material for studying Zhou's life and ideas, as well as
the history of the CPC and the country after the founding of New
China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
