<HEADLINE> New Customs House for East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, March 4 (Xinhua) --The customs office of the Economic
and Technological Development Zone of Hangzhou has just started
formal operation, announced Zhang Caiyue, head of the customs
office.
</P>
<P>
In 1993, preparations began to establish the customs office
around Hangzhou, the capital city of east China's Zhejiang
Province.
</P>
<P>
Since June of 1995 when it started to handle customs on a trial
basis, Zhang's office helped to levy 10 million yuan in tariffs.
</P>
<P>
Zhang believes that the formal operation of the customs office
will improve the investment environment in the development zone
and attract more overseas funds to the area.
</P>
<P>
The Hangzhou Economic and Technological Development Zone has
become a base for light industrial, food, electro-mechanical,
textile, pharmaceutical and chemical industrial production and is
listed among one of China's best economic and technological
development zones.
</P>
<P>
The zone attracted 1.2 billion U.S. dollars and generated two
billion yuan (one U.S. dollars equals to 8.3 Chinese currency) of
industrial output value last year.  
</P>
