<DOCNO> XIE19970304.0245 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Pig-Breeding Technique Fatten A Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, March 4 (Xinhua) -- A new breeding technique to rapidly
fatten pigs has helped increase profit by two billion yuan for
northeast China's Heilongjiang Province.
</P>
<P>
Designed to fatten pigs in low temperature, the technique marks
a "revolution" in pig-breeding in the cold areas in northern China.
</P>
<P>
Experts select suitable varieties of pigs and provide a warm
pigsty and mixed feed for them, thus enhancing the continual
growth of the stock through the winter.
</P>
<P>
In this way, mature pigs can be supplied to the market twice in
one year in cold areas, rather than previously once a year.
</P>
<P>
So far, 17 million pigs in Heilongjiang Province have been
raised using this technique.
</P>
<P>
The technique, created in 1990 in Heilongjiang, has been spread
to its neighboring Jilin Province and the Inner Mongolia Autonomous
Region. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
