<HEADLINE> ROK Becoming Weihai's Biggest Investment, Trade Partner </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WEIHAI, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Business interests from the
Republic of Korea (ROK) will invest more than 100 million
U.S. dollars this year in the coastal city of Weihai, Shandong
Province, according to local officals.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, Weihai City, which is separated from the ROC by the
sea, also hopes to chalk up 1.5 billion U.S. dollars worth of
imports and exports with the ROK, which has become the city's
largest investment and trade partner.
</P>
<P>
One of the earliest inland areas to have initiated cooperative
trade agreements with ROK businesses, Weihai City is now home to 566
ROK-financed businesses, according to a local government official.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the city approved 113 ROK directly funded ventures,
with contracts equivalent to 300 million U.S. dollars of ROK
investment.
</P>
<P>
The port city also traded 1.23 billion U.S. dollars worth of
imports and exports with ROK last year, accounting for about 60
percent of the city's total foreign trade volume. 
