<HEADLINE> Zhejiang Economy on Track of Sound Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The economy in east China's
Zhejiang Province, which has witnessed one of the country's
highest growth rates in recent years, is now firmly on a sound
track of development.
</P>
<P>
This is the result of years of work to transform the economic
growth mode from extensive operation to intensive operation, said
Provincial Governor Wan Xueyuan.
</P>
<P>
The economy in the coastal province grew 13 percent in 1996 to
register a GDP (gross domestic product) of 415 billion yuan, more
than three percent higher than the national average, while the
index of retail prices rose only 5.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang's financial revenues totalled 29.2 billion yuan last
year, up 17 percent. The per-capita income of urban and rural
residents averaged 6,345 yuan and 3,463 yuan, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The sound economic growth is also attributable to efforts to
boost the agricultural sector and optimize the industrial
structure, the governor said.
</P>
<P>
Over the past few years, chemicals, electronics,
telecommunications, pharmaceuticals and building materials have
grown into new pillar industries and economic growth areas of
Zhejiang.
</P>
<P>
The manufacturing industry increased its output value by 195
billion yuan in 1996, up 16 percent over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Continued improvement in infrastructures, particularly
transport facilities, has also stimulated the growth of the
province's economy, Wan added.
</P>
<P>
He pledged that this year, Zhejiang will continue to deepen
economic reforms and promote the transformation of the economic
growth mode, while quickening the pace of restructuring of
state-owned firms. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970304.0249 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dalian Has 6,004 Overseas-Backed Ventures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, March 4 (Xinhua) -- This coastal city of northeast
China's Liaoning Province, home to 6,004 overseas-financed
businesses, has so far used 4.17 billion U.S. dollars of foreign
funds.
</P>
<P>
According to local officials, overseas investment has poured
into Dalian, also a port city, over the past four years, with the
annual contractual sum increasing by two billion U.S. dollars. The
number of projects involving large amounts of overseas funds or
hi-tech or new technology has also been growing rapidly.
</P>
<P>
World-renowned companies or transnational corporations have
started more than 40 joint ventures with state-owned enterprises
and conglomerates in Dalian.
</P>
<P>
Local officials attributed the speedy inflow of overseas funds
into the city to Dalian's geographic advantages, good investment
environment and timely investment return.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, 2,850 overseas-backed ventures have
opened, demonstrating good economic efficiency. Last year, they
generated 28.1 billion yuan of output value, up 27 percent over
the previous year. More than 600 joint ventures have increased
investment, with the increased funds amounting to 2.1 billion
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The vast inflow of overseas funds has encouraged the growth of
Dalian's exports; the city is now exporting 18,000 kinds of
commodities, among which electro-mechanical goods hold the lion's
share of the city's total export volume. Export of technology has
also been increasing year by year.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, the city has been more actively seeking out
international economic and technological cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Dalian has conducted such cooperation with overseas companies
in the fields of architecture, fishery, shipping, foreign trade
and manufacturing. Business volume of the contracts signed by the
city for contracting projects overseas or for labor export
totalled 100 million U.S. dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Dalian's vibrant economy has advanced the city's
exchanges with the outside world.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the city received 210,000 overseas visitors,
including many foreign government officials and influential
celebrities. The city has also signed letters of intent for
friendly ties with Honolulu of the United States and Toronto of
Canada, and granted the title of "honorary citizen of Dalian" to
17 foreign citizens.  
</P>
