<HEADLINE> Guangxi to Speed Up Development of Tourist Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Southwest China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region plans to boost tourism in an effort to help more
than six million local people still under the poverty line to
increase their income.
</P>
<P>
Although an economically-disadvantaged area, Guangxi boasts
rich tourism resources, including an abundance of natural scenery
and local folklore. Some poverty-stricken counties have already
eradicated poverty by developing tourism, local authorities said.
</P>
<P>
Greater efforts should be made to develop basic tourist
facilities, such as transportation systems and hotels, as well as
exchanges of tourist information, they added.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government will offer preferential policies to
support local tourism development, the officials said. 
