<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Feature: Philippines' "Jollibee" Bites Back </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Working hard often means a success.
A Philippine "bee" has been busy working for two decades, and has
now defeated all its Western rivals in its own country.
</P>
<P>
"Jollibee"-- a "busy and happy bee," has become the largest
fast-food company in the Philippines after years of fierce
competition with Western companies.
</P>
<P>
Since it was incorporated in 1978 after starting modestly three
years earlier as a two-branch ice cream parlor, Jollibee Foods
Corp has been busy improving its aggressive marketing and
expansion strategy against its rivals in the Philippines, mainly
Mcdonald's, Kentucky Fried Chicken (KFC) and other Western
fast-food heavyweights. And now the strategy has put the company
at the top of the nation's fast-food industry.
</P>
<P>
Jollibee now has a total of 210 stores in the Philippines, and
25 in Asian and Mideast nations and regions, including Brunei,
Indonesia, Malaysia, Guam, Hong Kong, Vietnam, Saudi Arabia,
Kuwait and the United Arab Emirates, said Achie Sy, marketing
manager of Jollibee, in an interview today.
</P>
<P>
"We are planning to open six stores in California, the United
States, in the near future," she said.
</P>
<P>
Jollibee says it has 75 percent of the hamburger chain market
share and 55 percent of the fast-food sector in the country. In
the first nine months of 1996, the company posted 4.56 billion
pesos (174.17 million U.S. dollars) in revenues, a 32 percent
increase over the previous year.
</P>
<P>
However, the company will continue to aggressively pursue its
expansion program this year to bolster its stronghold in the local
fast-food industry and increase its presence in markets abroad.
</P>
<P>
In a recent statement, Jollibee said that it is slated to open
40 more branches nationwide this year. This will bring to 250 its
total number of fast-food outlets throughout the country.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, it said, the company is scheduled to open 20
more chains in the United States, Spain, Papua New Guinea and
other countries as part of its expansion program for 1997.
</P>
<P>
What is the secret of Jollibee's success? Just look at the
massive stripped orange-and-yellow bee which stands at the gate of
every Jollibee store and lures lots of kids away from Western
fast-food chains, says Jay Visco, marketing director of Jollibee
International.
</P>
<P>
That's the company's "secret weapon" against its rivals, Visco
said.
</P>
<P>
But obviously, there are other secrets behind Jollibee's
success. According to its executives, Jollibee's menu gives it the
edge over its Western rivals.
</P>
<P>
By offering a mixture of Western and localized fast-food, such
as hamburger, fried chicken and noodles, in the Philippines,
Jollibee has tried to make its taste more suited to Filipinos.
Jollibee's hamburger meat is blended with garlic and soya sauce
before cooking begins. That is different from the American food,
as Americans just grind the beef and cook it.
</P>
<P>
"Most Filipinos do not like the American food, which is hot and
has no taste. Our taste is more suited to local people," said
Achie Sy.
</P>
<P>
Jollibee also seasons fried chicken and spaghetti with sweet
sauce, the taste Filipinos like.
</P>
<P>
Abroad, Jollibee has studied the different taste of local
people and adjusted its manu accordingly, though overseas Jollibee
stores cater mainly for Filipinos working there.
</P>
<P>
Another secret for Jollibee's success is its good service for
customers. In any Jollibee store, one can get his food in one
minute after he places his order, and If one needs delivery, the
nearby Jollibee store would deliver its food to his doorsteps in
less than 30 minutes, the fast-food company claims.
</P>
<P>
Jollibee's success has stimulated its development at home and
abroad. In March 1996, the company earned master franchise rights
to Donut Magic, opening four outlets by the end of the year, and
in July 1996 it opened its first Mary's chicken restaurant.
</P>
<P>
In 1995, the company bought 40 Greenwich pizza outlets and has
since opened another 30.
</P>
<P>
Jollibee's success is amazing. Analysts here said that When
Western fast-food chains are holding larger and larger shares of
the Asian markets, the "busy and happy bee" (Jollibee) is biting
back.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
