<DOCNO> XIE19970304.0264 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Another Blast Rocks Newspaper Building in Karachi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 4 (Xinhua) -- A bomb went off outside the
offices of another major Urdu newspaper early today in Pakistan's
largest city of Karachi, but caused no casualties, sources said.
</P>
<P>
It was another bomb blast in the capital of the southern Sindh
province within just 24 hours.
</P>
<P>
The blast, which occurred outside a seven-storey building of
the Jang Group of newspapers, brought about a huge panic among the
staffs inside the offices, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
No group or people have claimed responsibility for the blast.
</P>
<P>
A time-bomb ripped through the office of the Urdu language
daily newspaper Qaumi Akhbar early Monday, slightly injuring two
employees and causing major property damage.
</P>
<P>
The damage caused by Monday's explosion is estimated by the
executive editor of the Qaumi Akhbar at 250,000 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif said on Monday that the incident
amounts to an attack on the freedom of the press and he ordered
Sindh provincial authorities to net the culprits as soon as
possible.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
