<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chile, Italy to Strengthen Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Italy's Foreign Trade Minister
Agusto Fantozzi offered today, following a meeting with Chilean
foreign minister Jose Insulza, to promote economic and trade
relations with Chile.
</P>
<P>
Fantozzi is visiting Chile at the head of a delegation of
Italian businessmen who have expressed interest in exploring
investment and trade opportunities with Chile and other countries
in the region.
</P>
<P>
Fantozzi told Insulza that Italy plans to promote economic and
trade relations with Chile with vigor.
</P>
<P>
According to Fantozzi, Chile is "a South American model for
Italy." Both countries, he said, have maintained "very good"
relations, which can be improved even more.
</P>
<P>
The Italian foreign trade minister also had talks with Chile's
Mining Minister benjamin Teplizky during which they were reported
to have discussed the possibility of Italian investment in mining
and other economic areas of this South American country.
</P>
<P>
Insulza agreed with Fantozzi and pointed out Chile aspires to
receive greater flows of Italian investments.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the trade volume between Chile and Italy
was about 1.2 billion U.S. dollars in 1996, that is equal to the
amount last year, and 3 times that of 1990. 
</P>
</TEXT>
