<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka's Amnesty For Illegal Weapons Ends Tonight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's amnesty for the
handover of illegal weapons ends tonight but police say that as
many as 3,297 weapons which have been issued irregularly to the
politicians during the last regime are still to be recovered.
</P>
<P>
In an effort to collect the weapons, the government declared
the amnesty on February 24 and since then police have been
deployed throughout the country to collect them. Only 180 weapons
have been recovered so far.
</P>
<P>
The exercise comes in the wake of widespread political violence
 connected with the run-up to the local government elections
scheduled for March 21.
</P>
<P>
According to the police, there have so far been 560
election-related violent incidents since February 11 when District
MP Nalanda Ellawala was killed in a clash between government
supporters and supporters of the main opposition United National
Party at Ratnapura, a town in the mid-country plantation region.
</P>
<P>
Police sources said that persons holding illegal weapons from
tomorrow will be arrested and prosecuted.
</P>
<P>
The unauthorized firearms comprising revolvers, pistols, shot
guns and repeater shot guns are those which were issued to
parliamentarians, provincial councilors and municipal and urban
councilors for self protection by the United National Party regime
during the southern uprising of Sinhalese youths.
</P>
<P>
They should have been returned after the uprising was
suppressed in 1989 but the politicians continued to hold them and
also distributed them among their supporters.
</P>
<P>
The growing political violence has induced political party
leaders to cooperate with the authorities and ensure the voluntary
surrender of arms.
</P>
<P>
A party leaders conference summoned Monday by the Speaker of
parliament K.B. Ratnayake resulted in a joint appeal by all party
leaders being issued to their supporters to cooperate with the
authorities and voluntarily surrender all unauthorized arms.
</P>
</TEXT>
