<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Trade Surplus Rises 45 Percent in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia posted a whopping 6.946
billion U.S. dollars trade surplus for 1996, up 45 percent from
the previous year, according to an official document.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, Indonesia's oil and gas trade surplus reached 8.149
billion dollars, but its non-oil and gas trade registered a
deficit of 1.203 billion dollars, the document released by the
Ministry of Industry and Trade Monday said.
</P>
<P>
In 1995, the country's oil and gas trade surplus was 7.553
billion dollars while its non-oil and gas deficit was 2.764
billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Trade surplus for last December stood at 916.1 million dollars,
down 10.2 percent from more than one billion dollars in December
1995, the document said.
</P>
<P>
Exports in December stood at 4.6 billion dollars, up 3.5
percent from the same month a year earlier and 6.2 percent up from
November, it said.
</P>
<P>
Imports in December stood at 3.8 billion dollars, up 7.5
percent from December in 1995 and 3.4 percent up from November,
said the document. 
</P>
</TEXT>
