<HEADLINE> Romania Initiates Establishment of Rapid Reaction Force </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Romania initiated today the
establishment of the country's first rapid reaction force designed
to provide disaster relief and participate in military operations
along with allied forces.
</P>
<P>
The Romanian National Defense Ministry held a ceremony in a
military area command in Dej in southern Romania to initiate the
establishment of the force, which will be placed under the direct
command of the headquarters of the general staff of the Romanian
army.
</P>
<P>
The special force, being set up in accordance with a decision
of the Supreme National Defense Council, will comprise a
mechanized unit, a tank unit, an artillery unit and an airborne
unit and will be equipped with modern weapons and installations.
</P>
<P>
The press bureau of the Romanian army said that basic missions
of this force are to fulfil tasks of national defense strategy,
provide disaster relief and curb regional military conflicts along
with NATO troops and troops of the countries that join NATO's
partnership for peace program.
</P>
<P>
With 20,000 officers and soldiers, the rapid reaction force
will be established in three years.
</P>
<P>
Romania will have become the ninth European country with a
rapid reaction force. 
</P>
</TEXT>
