<HEADLINE> More Space for Hi-tech Industry in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The hi-tech industrial
development zone in Hangzhou, the capital of east China's Zhejiang
Province, has been expanded to accommodate more hi-tech
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The zone has been developing rapidly in recent years, and by
1996 reported a total income of 5.2 billion yuan and exports worth
41 million US dollars, up 69 and 25 percent respectively over the
previous year.
</P>
<P>
Last year, 55 enterprises were approved for the development
zone, pushing the total number to 469, of which 226 are hi-tech
ones.
</P>
<P>
The area has limited development, an official said, noting that
authorities of the development zone had to shut the door on ten
enterprises last year, which promised to invest 50 million US
dollars there, because of limited space.
</P>
<P>
Under the circumstances, the municipal government decided to
allocate another 10.5 sq km of land to the development zone last
winter. 
</P>
