<HEADLINE> Great Role for Chinese Women in Poverty Relief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, March 4 (Xinhua) -- There is now one female skilled
worker per every 20 families in Sanya, a scenic city in south
China's Hainan Province.
</P>
<P>
Women are playing an important role in the poverty relief
efforts in the booming province, local officials said.
</P>
<P>
The provincial women's federation has launched a technical
training program to help women develop their work
capabilities. And in 1996, the organization sponsored 1,073
training classes involving agriculture techniques for planting
fruit trees and raising domestic animals and fish, with 61,997
women in attendance.
</P>
<P>
There are now 25,700 well-trained female farmers across
Hainan. A survey showed that more than 90 percent of them have
played an important role in helping other local women develop the
economy.
</P>
<P>
Last year, 87,700 women in the province were able to escape
poverty after learning some technical skills. 
</P>
