<HEADLINE> Facts &AMP; Figures: Road &AMP; Water Transport (5) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Some 11.4 Chinese people traveled
on roads across China last year, and passenger turnover reached
506 billion person-km, rising 9.5 percent and 9.9 percent
respectively from the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Road transport of cargo amounted to 10 billion tons, and the
cargo turnover 500 billion ton-km, up 6.4 percent and 6.5 percent
from 1995.
</P>
<P>
China built 25,000 km of highways last year, making the total
length of its highways 1.18 million km. Among the 3,258 km of
expressways China now has, 1,117 km of expressway were built last
year.
</P>
<P>
Last year, China's waterways carried 220 million passengers,
and the passenger turnover was 1.68 million person-km, down 7.9
percent and 2.2 percent respectively from 1995.
</P>
<P>
While water cargo transport reached 118.9 million tons, and
cargo turnover 1776 billion ton-km, up five percent and 1.2
percent from 1995.
</P>
<P>
China built 26 berths last year, adding a handling capacity of
3.4 million tons. And its main ports handled 1.155 billion tons of
cargos, rising 3.8 percent from 1995.  
</P>
</TEXT>
