<HEADLINE> Facts &AMP; Figures: Railway Industry (6) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- China's railways carried a total
of 942 million passengers and 1.62 billion tons of cargos last
year, down 12.3 percent and up 1.9 percent respectively from 1995.
</P>
<P>
China invested 32 billion yuan in railway construction. The
Ministry of Railways laid 1,300 km of tracks, including 436 km of
double tracks. And it completed the building of 1,980 km of new
rail lines, 1,500 km of double-track lines, and nearly 700 km of
electrified lines.
</P>
<P>
The railway industry also introduced 370 million US dollars
in overseas investment in 1996, including 155 million US dollars
in loans and 184 pieces of equipment purchased with overseas
funds.
</P>
<P>
On September 1, the Beijing-Kowloon railway, the third trunk
rail link between northern and southern China, went into service.
With a total investment of 40 billion, it is the most expensive
railway project China has ever carried out.  
</P>
