<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar Enacts National Food Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar State Law and Order
Restoration Council has enacted the National Food Law containing
12 chapters, according to today's official paper The New Light of
Myanmar.
</P>
<P>
The law is meant to enable the public to consume food of
genuine quality, free from danger and hygienic problems, and to
control and regulate the production, import, export, storage,
distribution and sale of food systematically, it is reported.
</P>
<P>
The law, which was enacted Monday, calls for formation of a
Food and Drug Authority to carry out the functions and duties.
</P>
<P>
Persons desirous of producing controlled food should obtain
licenses from the authority with recommendation from the Health
Department.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
