<HEADLINE> Facts &AMP; Figures for 1996: Chemical Industry (9) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- China's chemical industry yieled a
production value of 252 billion yuan in 1996, a 9.7 percent
year-on-year increase.
</P>
<P>
The industry produced a record 123 million tons of chemical
fertilizers, 8.4 percent more than the target set for the year.
The output for pesticides reached 350,000 tons, up 23.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
The output for other major chemical products are as follows:
ethylene, 3.01 millions, 118.0 percent of the target; chemical
fibers, 3.08 million tons,106.2 percent of the target.
</P>
<P>
Last year, a total of 72 large and medium-sized projects were
carried out, among which 16 were completed and put into operation.
</P>
<P>
Fourteen chemical industrial enterprises issued A shares,--
shares that are only traded by Chinese citizens. At present, a
total of 27 chemical enterprises are listed on both domestic and
overseas stock markets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
