<HEADLINE> Daqing Oil Company Entering International Prospecting Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The Geophysical Exploration Company
of the Daqing Petroleum Administration has signed a contract with
the US's Esso to gather seismic data in the Songliao Basin in
northeast China.
</P>
<P>
According to Xu Wenda, a senior engineer with the Daqing
company, his firm won a bid for deep-strata exploration, a risk
investment program in the northwestern part of Songliao Basin,
which was handled by the Esso Company China branch.
</P>
<P>
The contract stipulates that the Chinese firm will be
responsible for field operations and data for seismic exploration.
</P>
<P>
On completion of an on-the-spot inspection, experts from the
U.S. company said they believe the Chinese company has met all
requirements set by their company for collection and treatment of
seismic data, and has proven itself qualified for the job.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese firm has spent more than a month in completing the
task of field operations, which has been checked and accepted by
the US company, thus laying a foundation for increasing the
competitiveness of Daqing's seismic industry in the international
market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
