<BODY>
<HEADLINE> More Overseas Businessmen Investing in Southwest China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, March 4 (Xinhua) -- The southwestern China province of
Guizhou is now home to more than 1,000 overseas-financed ventures,
according to local sources.
</P>
<P>
Investors to this less developed Chinese province are mainly
from Hong Kong and Taiwan, who value the rich natural resources
and advantages there.Among 78 overseas-backed businesses registered
last year, 53 were started by Hong Kong and Taiwan businessmen.
</P>
<P>
Investment focuses on the industrial sector, including
processing of commodities from easily-obtained resources such as
timber and bamboo, paper-making, and chemical materials products.
</P>
<P>
Investment in real estate and the entertainment business has
dropped by a big margin. At the same time, solely overseas-funded
enterprises increased rapidly to 255 in the province, an increase
of 254 over 1989. 
</P>
</TEXT>
