<HEADLINE> Chinese, Chilean Deputy FMs hold talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The visiting Chinese Deputy
Foreign Minister, Li Zhaoxing, and his Chilean counterpart,
Mariano Fernandez, today held talks on bilateral relations and
international issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference after their two-hour meeting,
the two deputy foreign ministers said they reached agreements to
promote bilateral relations and strengthen economic, trade,
technological and cultural cooperation between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
They also agreed to continue their friendship and collaboration
in international organizations, including the United Nations and
in the Asia Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC), among others.
</P>
<P>
Li stressed that Chile had become China's second largest trade
partner in Latin America, and he believed there was still great
potential for further expanding trade.
</P>
<P>
Fernandez reiterated Chilean President Eduardo Frei's
invitation to Chinese President Jiang Zemin to visit Chile when it
is convenient for him.
</P>
<P>
Li Zhaoxing arrived here on Sunday for the three-day visit. He
will visit El Teniente copper mine in Rancagua tomorrow, and meet
Chilean Senate President Sergio Diez on Wednesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
