<HEADLINE> Facts &AMP; Figures for 1996: Steel Industry (10) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- China became the world's top steel
producer last year, with an annual output of 101.1 million tons,
or 105.3 percent of the planned target.
</P>
<P>
The output of steel plates, tubes and strips combined reached
32.53 million tons, up 10.7 percent over 1995.
</P>
<P>
Among the 107 state-owned large and medium-size steel
manufacturers, 70 percent made profits last year, and the total
net profit reached 5.1 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Chinese automakers turned out 1.49 million automobiles last
year, 96.1 percent of the planned target.  
</P>
</TEXT>
