<HEADLINE> Facts &AMP; Figures for 1996: Key Projects (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Progress of China's key capital
construction and major technological renovation projects sped up
in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The number of large and medium-sized capital construction
projects completed last year increased from the planned 97 to 134
by year-end, the largest in recent years.
</P>
<P>
Construction of the large projects such as the Three Gorges
Project, the world's largest water conservancy program, have
proceeded smoothly.
</P>
<P>
The investment for the less-developed central and western China
accounted for more than 43 percent of the total investment in the
major projects launched in the year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
