<HEADLINE> Facts &AMP; Figures for 1996: Overseas Investment (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- Actual overseas investment in
China grew 12.2 percent to 42.35 billion US dollars last year
despite a drop in the number of approved overseas-funded projects.
</P>
<P>
Overseas-sourced loans totaled 16 billion US dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
Overseas investment in China has stabilized at a high level
over recent years.
</P>
<P>
As China readjusts its policy on the use of overseas
investment, the part directed to infrastructure and basic
industries and to less developed central and western China is on
the rise. 
</P>
</TEXT>
