<BODY>
<HEADLINE> IOC May Adopt Blood Test in Fighting Doping </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, May 3 (Xinhua) -- The International Olympic Committee
(IOC) may adopt blood test to fight doping, IOC official said in
Lausanne on Monday.
</P>
<P>
IOC doping expert Patrick Schamasch said the blood test has
been experimented in the recent Nordic skiing world championships.
</P>
<P>
Blood was taken from skiers before the race and if the levels
of haemoglobin were too high, the skiers would be banned from the
competitions.
</P>
<P>
Schamasch said he was following closely the developments and he
thought that the international skiing officials might ask for
blood tests to be used for the first time at the 1998 Nagano
Winter Olympic Games. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
