<HEADLINE> Sjoberg Skips World Indoor Athletics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Sweden's former world outdoor
high jump champion Patrick Sjoberg announced on Monday that he
had withdrawn from this week's World Indoor Athletics
Championships which start in Paris on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The 32-year-old Sjoberg, a former world record holder, said he
had not recovered from consistent painful cramps in his calves.
</P>
<P>
Sjoberg, who won the 1987 World title in Rome, was attacked by
a female rock singer in a bar here on February 22. The woman
threw a glass at Sjoberg, leaving him with a cut that required
nine stitches.
</P>
<P>
Sjoberg, a triple Olympic medallist, said he was thinking of
suing for damages. After that horrible incident, he left Sweden
for Spain to take his outdoor season training. 
</P>
</TEXT>
