<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Facts &AMP; Figures: Energy Industry (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- China produced a record 156.45
million tons of crude oil in 1996, some eight million tons more
than in the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Eighty percent of the production was made from oil fields on
land, which turned out 141.41 million tons of crude oil and 16.44
billion cubic meters of natural gas, 1.6 million tons and 290
million cu m more than in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Daqing Oil Field remained the top producer with 56 million tons
of oil, while newly developed oil fields in the remote west region
of Xinjiang turned out 15.4 million tons, 2.56 million tons more
than in 1995.
</P>
<P>
Crude from offshore fields exceeded 14 million tons, a 66
percent increase over 1995. Offshore natural gas output exceeded
three billion cu m, more than seven times the previous year's
figure.
</P>
<P>
Coal output reached 1.26 billion tons of standard coal, 106.2
percent of the target.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
