<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Facts &AMP; Figures for 1996: Power Industry (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 4 (Xinhua) -- China generated a record 1075
billion kilowatts-hours (KWh) of electricity in 1996, growing 6.8
percent over 1995, and completing 100.5 percent of the pre-set
target.
</P>
<P>
Thermal power plants - coal and gas fired - produced 875.7
billion KWh of electricity, up 8.5 percent over 1995;
hydroelectric power stations produced 185 billion KWh of
electricity, leveling the previous year's level; and nuclear power
stations generated 14.3 billion KWh of electricity.
</P>
<P>
An installed capacity totaling 15 million KW, and
5,477 km of power transmission lines with voltage over 220
kilovolts were added last year.
</P>
<P>
A total of 93.03 billion yuan was invested in large and
medium-sized power projects, in which 36.55 billion yuan were
state investment, 10.68 billion yuan overseas funds, and the rest
investment by enterprises and local bodies.  
</P>
</TEXT>
