<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysian Corporate Helicopter Crashes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 4 (Xinhua) -- A corporate helicopter
crashed near Kuala Lipis in the state of Negeri Pahang Monday
night with the fate of three persons on board uncertain, the
Department of Civil Aviation (DCA) said today.
</P>
<P>
The aircraft, an Augusta-109 belonging to Gadek Aviation, was
on a flight from here to Kuala Terengganu on the east coast of the
peninsular Malaysia, DCA Director-General Haji Zaini Omar said in
a statement.
</P>
<P>
Police confirmed sighting the wreckage of the helicopter and
rescue operations were being undertaken by the Kuala Lipis police.
Kuala Lipis is about 170 kilometers northeast of here.
</P>
<P>
"At this juncture we are not certain of the fate of the pilot
and the occupants on board the helicopter," Zaini said.
</P>
<P>
The helicopter was cruising at 2,727 meters and under radar
control.
</P>
<P>
Upon loss of radar contact with the helicopter, the Kuala
Lumpur Rescue Coordination Center was activated and it immediately
launched search and rescue operations.
</P>
<P>
Zaini said the DCA also sought the assistance of passing
aircraft to try to establish communications with the helicopter.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
