<HEADLINE> Angolan Women to Support Government of National </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Secretary-general of the
Organization of Angolan Women Ruth Neto said here today that the
Angolan government of national unity and reconciliation to be
formed will improve living standards of its people, especially
those of women and children.
</P>
<P>
She made the remarks in northeastern city Saurimo, Angola on
the 30th anniversary of the establishment of the organization,
according to Angola's national news agency.
</P>
<P>
The secretary-general said that her organization will support
the new government by promoting the realization of peace and
national reconciliation and helping the reunion of those families
broken by war in the country.
</P>
<P>
Neto urged the new government to improve the state of the most
vulnerable social class, especially the old and children and
enhance the status of women.
</P>
<P>
She called for the protection of rights of women as they play
a very important role in a country's changes, the report said.
</P>
</TEXT>
